out Office Transport Services All about Office Transport Services All about Office Transport Services All about Office Transport Services All about Office Transport Services <br>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-08-24 12:54:19','smallCONT-00116page3-img2.jpg','midCONT-00116page3-img2.jpg','bigCONT-00116page3-img2.jpg','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00117',NULL,'ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â‚¬ÂÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¾ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚ÂºÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â§ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â','Excerpted from How to Grow Practically Everything','<h1 style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.75pt;margin-left:\r\n0in;background:white\"><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 16.5pt;\">No matter how good\r\nyour soil, it will probably need extra nutrients to help plants with specific\r\nneeds, or to boost them at key times, like flowering. Always follow the\r\ninstructions on the label because too much, or the wrong type of fertilizer,\r\ncan cause problems, such as plants with all leaves and no flowers.</span></h1>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:4.5pt;line-height:17.25pt;mso-outline-level:\r\n2;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:16.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Understanding\r\nNutrients<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">The three basic\r\nelements that plants require are nitrogen (N), phosphorus (P) and potassium\r\n(K). Nitrogen is needed for leaf and shoot growth, phosphorus for roots, and\r\npotassium helps flowers and fruits develop. Fertilizer manufacturers list the\r\nnutrient content as a ratio: a general purpose fertilizer has an N:P:K ratio of\r\n7:7:7, while a tomato feed has a high concentration of potassium to boost fruit\r\nproduction, and a fertilizer for lawns or leafy crops contains mostly nitrogen.\r\nMany fertilizers also include various trace elements or micronutrients. A\r\nplant&acute;s nutrient requirements can depend on its growth phase, with most needing\r\na general boost in the spring, and additional potassium as they fruit or\r\nflower.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Nitrogen (nitrate) is\r\nneeded for healthy leaves.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Potassium (potash)\r\nboosts the production of flowers and fruit.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">For strong root\r\ndevelopment, choose a fertilizer rich in phosphorus (phosphate).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:15.75pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n16.5pt;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\"></span></p><div><img src=\"adminppl/contentimage/13Feeding Image 1.jpg\" alt=\"\" alignment=\"left\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\"></div><a href=\"http://www.hgtv.com/gardening/feeding-your-plants/index.html?ic1=obinsite\"><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#386cb4;text-decoration:none;=\"\" text-underline:none\"=\"\"></span></a><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#444444\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:15.75pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n16.5pt;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://www.hgtv.com/gardening/feeding-your-plants/index.html?ic1=obinsite\"><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#386cb4;text-decoration:none;=\"\" text-underline:none\"=\"\">Image 2</span></a><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#444444\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l3 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://www.hgtv.com/gardening/feeding-your-plants/index.html?ic1=obinsite\"><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#386cb4;text-decoration:none;=\"\" text-underline:none\"=\"\">Image 3</span></a><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#444444\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:5.25pt;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#999999\"=\"\">DK -&nbsp;<i>How to Grow Practically Everything</i>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â© 2010\r\nDorling Kindersley Limited</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\r\n\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:4.5pt;line-height:17.25pt;mso-outline-level:\r\n2;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:16.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Fertilizer Choices<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Your local garden\r\ncenter will offer both organic (derived from plants and animals) and\r\ninorganic(chemically manufactured) fertilizers. Most are concentrated for\r\nconvenience and available as liquids, powders that you dilute in water, or\r\ngranules. Typical examples of organic fertilizers are pelleted chicken manure;\r\nblood, fish, and bonemeal; liquid seaweed fertilizer; and homemade plant feeds,\r\nsuch as the diluted liquor from a wormery, or fertilizers made from soaking\r\ncomfrey leaves. Inorganic feeds include sulfate of potash, Growmore, and\r\ngranular rose feeds.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Blood, fish, and\r\nbonemeal (image 1) is a balanced organic fertilizer, applied through the\r\ngrowing season around flowers and vegetables; cease applications in early\r\nautumn.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Slow-release granules\r\n(image 2), activated by warmth and moisture, give a steady supply of nutrients\r\nin containers and borders.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Well-rotted manure or\r\ngarden compost (image 3) is rich in trace elements and soil-conditioning\r\nsubstances. Dig it in or apply as a surface mulch.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Growmore (image 4) is\r\na balanced chemical feed used to enrich soil for sowing or planting, and as a\r\ntop dressing.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:15.75pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n16.5pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://www.hgtv.com/gardening/feeding-your-plants/index.html?ic1=obinsite\"><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#386cb4;text-decoration:none;=\"\" text-underline:none\"=\"\">Image 1</span></a><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#444444\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:15.75pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n16.5pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in;background:w