le=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:white;text-decoration:none;=\"\" text-underline:none\"=\"\">+</span></a><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#999999\"=\"\">DK -&nbsp;<i>How to Grow Practically Everything</i>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â© 2010\r\nDorling Kindersley Limited</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\r\n\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:4.5pt;line-height:17.25pt;mso-outline-level:\r\n2;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:16.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Decorative Options<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Mulches that don&acute;t\r\ndecompose are useful as decorative garden surfaces. They are particularly\r\neffective when laid over landscape fabric or membrane, which reduces weed\r\ngrowth and helps prevent soil mixing in with the mulch and spoiling the effect.\r\nFor a modern feel, try colored crushed glass or slate shards. Cover small\r\nareas, like the tops of pots and containers, with beads, crushed and whole\r\nshells, or polished pebbles. Natural pebbles blend well with gravel over larger\r\nareas, and can create a beach effect when laid in swathes.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Pebbles (image 1) come\r\nin different colors and sizes. Ask to see a sample out of the bag, wetted to\r\nshow the true color.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Crushed glass (image\r\n2) is usually a recycled product, milled to take off the sharp edges. Use\r\nbright colors for design highlights.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Slate chips (image 3)\r\nin various grades and subtle shades of dark gray have sharp edges, so they are\r\nunsuitable for children&acute;s areas.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Crushed shells (image\r\n4) are recycled from the seafood industry.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:15.75pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n16.5pt;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo7;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb