te\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://www.hgtv.com/gardening/feeding-your-plants/page-2.html\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:white;text-decoration:none;=\"\" text-underline:none\"=\"\">+</span></a><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#999999\"=\"\">DK -&nbsp;<i>How to Grow Practically Everything</i>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â© 2010\r\nDorling Kindersley Limited</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\r\n\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-08-31 10:14:52','smallCONT-00117Feeding your plants.jpg','midCONT-00117Feeding your plants.jpg','bigCONT-00117Feeding your plants.jpg','USR-000001','2013-11-26 05:10:33','USR-000001',3),('CONT-00118',NULL,'Draft Gardening Improvisation Tips','Solve gardening problems and make your gardening experience easier.','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 9.75pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><img src=\"http://198.8.83.157/pepeelika/adminppl/contentimage/smallCONT-00118Gardening%20Improvisation%20Tips.jpg\"></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 9.75pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 16.5pt;\">Little tips and tricks\r\nhere and there can make gardening easier. Master gardener Paul James offers\r\nsuggestions to help solve some of your gardening problems:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Shoveling is hard\r\nwork, but it&acute;s often even harder when clay soil sticks to the shovel, forcing\r\nyou to stop and scrape off the clay. The solution? Rub a light coat of floor or\r\ncar wax over the metal surface with a cloth and buff lightly. Waxing also prevents\r\nrust from forming and even prevents snow from sticking to snow shovels.</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Apply a light coat of\r\nwax to your mower&acute;s metal and plastic surfaces and buff well with a clean, dry\r\ncloth. The wax will protect the mower from the elements and prevent grass clippings\r\nand dirt from sticking to it, which makes cleanup a breeze.</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">To keep track of your\r\nlong-handled tools when working in the garden, cut a 4- to 6-inch wide piece of\r\nPVC pipe to a length of about four feet. In an out-of-the-way spot in or near\r\nyour garden, dig a hole with a post-hole digger about a foot deep. Place the\r\npipe in the hole and pack soil around it. Put your tools in the pipe, and\r\nyou&acute;ll always know where they are. You can also paint the pipe brown or green\r\nto blend in with its surroundings. To keep leaves out of the pipe when you&acute;re\r\nnot working in the garden, top off the pipe with a PVC cap.<br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Use an old golf bag to\r\ncarry long-handled tools to and from the garden. Some golf bags have a built-in\r\nstand, which makes grabbing tools a breeze. You can use the pockets on the bag\r\nto hold all sorts of gardening items as well as various refreshments.</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Use a bucket or basket\r\nto carry hand tools.</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#444444\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">To make an old rain\r\ngauge easy to read from a distance, just add a few drops of food coloring. Each\r\ntime you empty the gauge, add a few fresh drops and occasionally change the\r\ncolor.</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#444444\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:10.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">To remember where you\r\nwant to plant spring-flowering bulbs in the fall or early winter, first\r\ndetermine exactly where you want the bulbs to go. Then dig individual planting\r\nholes at the proper spacing for the bulb you have in mind. Place four-inch\r\nplastic pots in the holes up to their rims, and fill each with the excavated\r\nsoil. Next fall, planting will be as simple as removing each pot, placing a\r\nbulb in the hole, and covering the hole with soil in the pot. Make sure you\r\nplant the pots so that they are barely above soil level so you won&acute;t run over\r\nthem with the lawnmower. This is a great way to ensure that next year you will\r\nget those bulbs in the ground on time.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-08-31 11:56:09','smallCONT-00118Gardening Improvisation Tips.jpg','midCONT-00118Gardening Improvisation Tips.jpg','bigCONT-00118Gardening Improvisation Tips.jpg','USR-000001','2013-08-31 11:56:50','USR-000001',8),('CONT-00119',NULL,'Draft 10 Tips for Involving Kids with Urban Chickens','About Involving Kids with Urban Chickens','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n13.5pt;mso-outline-level:1;background:white\"><img src=\"http://198.8.83.157/pepeelika/adminppl/contentimage/smallCONT-0011910%20Tips%20for%20Involving%20Kids%20with%20Urban%20Chickens.jpg\"></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n13.5pt;mso-outline-level:1;background:white\"><span style=\"line-height: 13.5pt; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(76, 51, 39);\">Thinking about keeping chickens in the city?\r\nSo are many other families! Raising urban chickens will not only provide your\r\nfamily with nutritious farm-fresh eggs on a regular basis, but it can also be a\r\ngreat hands-on learning experience for your little farmers. Listed below are\r\nsome of our favorite ways to involve kids with your new brood members. If your\r\nfamily&acute;s just getting started raising city chickens, check out our</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.5pt; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(76, 51, 39);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.5pt; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(76, 51, 39);\"><a href=\"http://www.parentmap.com/article/keeping-chickens-in-the-city\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:#4C3327\">full\r\nguide for beginners</span></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">1.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">Kids have a ton of fun collecting eggs each day. And, if you\r\nhave too many eggs for your family to consume, they will share with pride any\r\nextras with friends and neighbors.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\r\n\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">We\r\nkeep dedicated \"chicken shoes\" by the back door, since coops equal\r\npoops, and you don&acute;t want your wee ones to track that stuff into the house.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">2.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">Obviously, helping you cook up some eggs is a great way for kids\r\nto gain an appreciation for where food comes from.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">3.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">Chickens are cool! Your kids&acute; friends ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â and most of the\r\nneighborhood ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â will want to see your pet chickens. Amaze your visitors with fun\r\nfacts like: \"Did you know that chickens are the closest living relatives\r\nof dinosaurs?\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">4.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">Teaching kids about pet care ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â like feeding and watering hens ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â\r\ncan be a way to model responsibility. Luckily chickens are as low-maintenance a\r\npet as you&acute;ll ever find. Baby chicks do take more care and a gentle touch ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â\r\nattendance to their needs is best assigned to older children or closely\r\nsupervised young ones.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">5.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">Most fun for everyone is giving chickens treats: Call them and\r\nthey&acute;ll come running! (But know that a bold hen might snatch a cracker out of\r\nthe hand of an inattentive toddler.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">6.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">Chickens raised as pets grow used to being handled and picked\r\nup, which is great fun. But, unlike cats or dogs, chickens are also fine\r\nwithout social interaction.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">7.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">With little ones: Have fun together reading chicken-themed books\r\nwith your child and singing farm-themed songs. Before she could walk, I used to\r\nhold my baby up so that she could reach inside the nest box to grab the eggsÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Âa\r\nbig thrill for her.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">8.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">Did I mention chicken costumes for Halloween? I&acute;ve used this\r\nMartha Stewart make-it-yourself kids&acute;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.marthastewart.com/271882/animal-costumes-chicken-costume-lamb-cos?czone=holiday/halloween-center/halloween-center-costumes&amp;page=3&amp;center=276965&amp;gallery=274791&amp;slide=229653\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:#4C3327\">chicken\r\ncostume</span></a>with great success.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">9.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">With older kids, make a book together about your own chickens ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â\r\ninclude drawings, chicken \"handprints,\" photos, list their favorite\r\ntreats, and write stories about their escapades. You could also consider\r\ngetting them involved in a 4H group (or start your own), like Sustainable Wallingford&acute;s\r\n\"<a href=\"http://greenwallingford.ning.com/group/4hclub\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:#4C3327\">Cooped Up in Seattle</span></a>\"\r\n4H club for urban farm kids.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:13.5pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">10.</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#4c3327\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:#4c3327\"=\"\">Take your kids with you on the Seattle Tilth&acute;s annual chicken\r\ncoop tour in July to meet other families with backyard chickens. Better yet,\r\nget on the coop tour and show off your own little ranch!<o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-08-31 12:17:17','smallCONT-0011910 Tips for Involving Kids with Urban Chickens.jpg','midCONT-0011910 Tips for Involving Kids with Urban Chickens.jpg','bigCONT-0011910 Tips for Involving Kids with Urban Chickens.jpg','USR-000001','2013-08-31 12:17:47','USR-000001',22),('CONT-00120',NULL,'Draft How to Cultivate and Care for Bonsai Trees','Learn these botanical basics to fully succeed at planting and caring for your bonsai tree.','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 9.75pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"></p><div><a href=\"http://198.8.83.157/pepeelika/krishi-bangla/content.php?ContentID=CONT-00117&amp;CID=SMN-0037&amp;menutype=submenu&amp;homemiddletype=\"><img src=\"adminppl/contentimage/14How to Cultivate and Care for Bonsai Trees.jpg\" alt=\"\" alignment=\"absmiddle\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\"></a></div><br><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Bonsai is said to be\r\nan art form, but you still have to have some botanical basics to be successful.\r\nBonsai is essentially a tree in a tiny tray; you can even train other types of\r\nplants.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Pruning, bending,\r\ntying and repotting all help keep the tree compact. Interestingly, if you were\r\nto take a bonsai tree and plant it in the landscape, it would grow into a\r\nregular-sized tree again. That, of course, defeats the purpose of the art but\r\npoints out an important aspect. Bonsai are not houseplants. \"They grow in\r\nnature outdoors, so you really need to keep them in their natural\r\nenvironment,\" says bonsai expert Dolly Fassio.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Many kinds of plants\r\ncan be trained to be bonsai. Dolly suggests beginning with a one-gallon,\r\ncontainer-grown plant purchased from a reputable nursery, preferably one that\r\nspecializes in bonsai. \"You need to get a tree that&acute;s easy to take care of\r\nin your area so you know that it will live in you environment.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">There are five basic\r\nbonsai styles:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:21.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">The formal upright\r\nstyle highlights a straight trunk<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:21.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">The informal upright\r\nstyle is curved and moving<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:21.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">A slanted trunk flows\r\ngracefully to one side, and a variation of this style is called\r\n\"windswept\" for obvious reasons<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:21.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">A half- or\r\nsemi-cascade drapes over the pot<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:21.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:16.5pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#444444\">ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">A full cascade drapes\r\nbeyond the pot&acute;s rim.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\"><br>\r\nThe tree itself will often dictate the bonsai style. But don&acute;t forget its\r\ncontainer. The bonsai pot should blend with the tree and add value and\r\ninterest. Containers vary in size and price.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">The foundation to\r\nbonsai is the soil. Bonsai trees need a special soil because they&acute;re confined\r\nto small pots. Use volcanic mixes containing pumice, fir bark and lava rock for\r\na well-draining soil. The roots hit the sharp edges of the pumice and form more\r\nhairlike roots. Fine hairlike roots are better for the tree&acute;s health than large\r\nroots, says bonsai enthusiast Fred Fassio.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">All bonsai need to be\r\nrepotted periodically. Eventually the roots will grow in and fill the pot. At\r\nthis point the tree is root-bound and can&acute;t absorb enough moisture. Repotting\r\nis an art form itself, and this Asian skill calls for Asian tools. Upon pulling\r\nthe plant out of its pot, Fred uses a chopstick to separate the roots. It&acute;s\r\nbest to repot during the tree&acute;s dormancy period since cutting the roots\r\nactually encourages new growth. Cut off approximately one-third of the roots\r\nfrom the bottom and around all the sides of the rootball.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">In nature, a taproot\r\nanchors the tree in the ground. With bonsai, wire does the trick. Thread wire\r\nthrough small holes in the pot. Next, add some soil around the rootball and\r\ngently twist the tree downward into the soil to get as much of it into the\r\ntree&acute;s roots as possible. Tighten the wire over the tree&acute;s larger roots, clip\r\naway the wire, and tighten it again securely. If the roots are properly wired\r\nin the pot, you should be able to pick the tree up by the trunk, and it won&acute;t\r\ncome out of its pot.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:12.0pt;line-height:16.5pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#444444\"=\"\">Add a few more scoops\r\nof soil over the roots and use a chopstick to push the soil down into the\r\ntree&acute;s roots. This eliminates air pockets that can damage or even kill the\r\ntree. The finishing touch is a layer of pre-moistened moss; this helps to add\r\nbeauty and maintain moisture.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-08-31 12:26:29','smallCONT-00120How to Cultivate and Care for Bonsai Trees.jpg','midCONT-00120How to Cultivate and Care for Bonsai Trees.jpg','bigCONT-00120How to Cultivate and Care for Bonsai Trees.jpg','USR-000001','2013-08-31 10:13:27','USR-000001',7),('CONT-00121',NULL,'Travel Bangladesh','Quick Look Bangladesh','<font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"2\">Location: \r\n      Southern Asia, bordering the Bay of Bengal, between Burma and India.<br>\r\n      Geographic coordinates: 24 00 N, 90 00 E.<br>\r\n      Map references: Asia<br>\r\n      Area:<br>\r\n      total: 144,000 sq km.<br>\r\n      land: 133,910 sq km.<br>\r\n      water: 10,090 sq km.<br>\r\n      Area-comparative: slightly smaller than Iowa.<br>\r\n      Land boundaries:<br>\r\n      total: 4,246 km<br>\r\n      border countries: Burma 193 km, India 4,053 km<br>\r\n      Coastline: 580 km.<br>\r\n      Maritime claims:<br>\r\n      contiguous zone: 18 nm.<br>\r\n      Continental shelf: up to the outer limits of the continental margin.<br>\r\n      Exclusive economic zone: 200 nm.<br>\r\n      Territorial sea: 12 nm.<br>\r\n      Climate: tropical; mild winter (October to March); hot, humid summer (March \r\n      to June); humid, warm rainy monsoon (June to October)<br>\r\n      Terrain: mostly flat alluvial plain; hilly in southeast.<br>\r\n      Elevation extremes:<br>\r\n      lowest point: Indian Ocean 0 m.<br>\r\n      highest point: Keokradong 1,230 m.<br>\r\n      Natural resources: natural gas, arable land, and timber.<br>\r\n      Land use:<br>\r\n      arable land: 61%<br>\r\n      permanent crops: 3%<br>\r\n      other: 36% (1998 est.)<br>\r\n      Irrigated land: 38,440 sq km (1998 est.)<br>\r\n      Natural hazards: droughts, cyclones; much of the country routinely flooded \r\n      during the summer monsoon season.<br>\r\n      Environment-current issues: many people are landless and forced to live \r\n      on and cultivate flood-prone land; limited access to potable water; water-borne \r\n      diseases prevalent; water pollution especially of fishing areas results \r\n      from the use of commercial pesticides; intermittent water shortages because \r\n      of falling water tables in the northern and central parts of the country; \r\n      soil degradation; deforestation; severe overpopulation.<br>\r\n      Environment-international agreements:<br>\r\n      party to: Biodiversity, Climate Change, Climate Change-Kyoto Protocol, Desertification, \r\n      Endangered Species, Environmental Modification, Hazardous Wastes, Law of \r\n      the Sea, Nuclear Test Ban, Ozone Layer Protection, Wetlands signed, but \r\n      not ratified: none of the selected agreements<br>\r\n      Transnational Issues<br>\r\n      Disputes-international: Only a small portion of the boundary with India \r\n      remains undelimited; discussions to demarcate the boundary, exchange 162 \r\n      miniscule enclaves, and allocate divided villages remain stalled; skirmishes, \r\n      illegal border trafficking, and violence along the border continue; Bangladesh \r\n      has protested India&acute;s attempts to fence off high traffic sections of the \r\n      porous boundary; Burmese attempts to construct a dam on the border stream \r\n      in 2001 prompted an armed response halting construction; Burmese Muslim \r\n      refugees migrate into Bangladesh straining meager resources.<br>\r\n      </font> \r\n\r\n    ','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-09-01 03:24:54','smallCONT-00121m_1025579c.jpg','midCONT-00121m_1025579c.jpg','bigCONT-00121m_1025579c.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',3),('CONT-00122',NULL,'Discover USA','Summer Work and Travel USA Program','Summer Work&amp;Travel USA program has \r\nbeen immensely popular among students all over the world for decades. It\r\n is one of the Cultural Exchange Programs for international students, \r\nsupported by the USA government. The application process is open for \r\nuniversity students aged between 18 and 27, who have good skills in \r\nEnglish language and are ready to meet all <a href=\"http://www.discover-ua.com/Education-in-Ukraine/study-overseas/Work-Travel-USA/W-T-Program-Description.html\">program requirements</a>.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The participants will spend their summer\r\n break working in the USA service companies, learning about American \r\nculture and lifestyle, improving their conversational skills in English,\r\n and vacation-traveling before they return home. Our company assists \r\nparticipants in all steps of the program, before and during their stay \r\nin the USA. To learn more about the program, please read the following \r\ninformation-</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-09-01 03:29:15','smallCONT-00122Work_Travel_USA_2009.jpg','midCONT-00122Work_Travel_USA_2009.jpg','bigCONT-00122Work_Travel_USA_2009.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',13),('CONT-00123',NULL,'Destination Dhaka','Welcome to Dhaka','\r\n                 \r\n                  \r\n                     \r\n                       \r\n                        <p><font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"2\"><b>DHAKA \r\n                          DIVISION</b></font></p>\r\n                        <p> </p>\r\n                        <p><font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"2\">Dhaka \r\n                          division is located at center of the country has an \r\n                          area of 31119 sq. km and a population of 38.678 million. \r\n                          It has 17 districts and 64 municipalities.</font> <font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"2\">Main \r\n                          rivers of this division are padma, jamuna, meghna, old \r\n                          brahmaputra, dhaleshwari, shitalakshya, brahmaputra, \r\n                          buriganga, arial khan. Madhupur and Bhawal Garhs are \r\n                          located to the northern parts of Dhaka, in Gazipur, \r\n                          southern part of Mymensingh and eastern part of Tangail \r\n                          districts; Garo hills are located in Mymens