p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Oil for deep-frying</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Toss the bitter gourd and potatoes with \r\nturmeric and salt and set aside for 15 min. Then drain the vegetables in\r\n a colander. This extracts some liquid from the bitter gourd and reduces\r\n its bitterness. Heat the oil in a thin walled wok till it is smoking.&nbsp; \r\nThen add the bitter gourd and potatoes in batches to the oil (be \r\ncareful- if you have left too much moisture in the vegetables, the oil \r\ncould spatter).&nbsp; Deep fry until the vegetables are browned and cooked \r\nthrough. If you use a cast iron wok, this should only take about 5 min. \r\nper batch.<br></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-10-31 05:18:32','smallCONT-00127life-korolla.jpg','midCONT-00127life-korolla.jpg','bigCONT-00127life-korolla.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:09:16','USR-000001',19),('CONT-00128',NULL,'Khichuri(rice, lentils)',' Traditional Bangladeshi Foods','The ultimate comfort food, Khichuri. A hearty and satisfying, single dish\r\n meal of rice, lentils, potatoes and brinjal. Khichuri is very popular \r\ndish of Bangladesh. In Bengal, cooks and homemakers often prepare this \r\ndish with many ingredients mixed with it. That is one of the reasons the\r\n idiom joga khichuri is used in Bangla to mean mess. In Bengali \r\ntradition it is customary... 						\r\n						','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-10-31 05:23:40','smallCONT-00128life-khichuri.jpg','midCONT-00128life-khichuri.jpg','bigCONT-00128life-khichuri.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:21:29','USR-000001',1),('CONT-00129',NULL,'Chingri Malai Curry','','Step 1: Raw Shrimp: De-vein the shrimp and then apply turmeric and salt.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>Ingredients: Thinly sliced Tomato (1), Coriander Leaves (8-10), Bay Leaves (2-3), Whole Cumin (1 tsp) , Whole Coriander Seeds (1 tsp), Cardamom (1 stick), Green Chillies (2)<br><br>Step 2: Ingredients: Thinly sliced Tomato (1), Coriander Leaves (8-10), Bay Leaves (2-3), Whole Cumin (1 tsp) , Whole Coriander Seeds (1 tsp), Cardamom (1 stick), Green Chillies (2), COCONUT MILK (200 ml, not shown here) and Salt to Taste<br>Heat 4 tb sp of Mustard Oil or Safflower Oil for 2-3 mins, then add whole cumin seeds, coriander seeds, cardamom, and bay leaves.<br><br>Step 3: Heat 4 tb sp of Mustard Oil or Safflower Oil for 2-3 mins, then add whole cumin seeds, coriander seeds, cardamom, and bay leaves. Then add the Shrimps. Fry the Shrimps till it turns light yellow. Then add Salt to taste.<br>Step 4: Add Tomato, Green Chillies and Coconut Milk. Let the Shrimps cook for 10 mins.<br><br>Step 4: Add Tomato, Green Chillies and Coconut Milk.<br>Serve this dish with plain rice.<br><br>Step 5: Let the Shrimps cook in medium heat for 10-12 mins. Serve this dish with plain rice. <br>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-10-31 05:56:35','smallCONT-00129life-chingri-malai-curry.jpg','midCONT-00129life-chingri-malai-curry.jpg','bigCONT-00129life-chingri-malai-curry.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:08:50','USR-000001',7),('CONT-00130',NULL,'What Is The Best Non-Prescription Eyelash Enhancer?','','<h1 style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:\r\n0in;background:white;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 16.5pt; font-weight: normal;\">Eyelash enhancers are\r\nthe latest beauty trend these days, and cosmetic companies everywhere are\r\nlaunching products that promise to give women longer, fuller, and darker lashes\r\nwithout the fuss of mascara or false lashes.&nbsp; But, with all these options,\r\nit&acute;s hard to know what really works and what doesn&acute;t.</span></h1>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">Luckily, there\r\nare&nbsp;reputable beauty sites out there that have put many of these eyelash\r\nenhancers to the test.&nbsp; The results for this year&acute;s top-performing eyelash\r\nenhancers are in ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦ with SmartLash coming in with a solid 5-star rating on\r\nDermStore.com, the #1 online destination for skin care and beauty.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">What Is Eyelash\r\nEnhancement?</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;\r\ncolor:#222222\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">If you aren&acute;t yet\r\naware of this increasingly popular method of achieving longer lashes, eyelash\r\nenhancers are formulas that are topically applied to the base of your lower and\r\nupper lashes.&nbsp; They can even be used on sparse, thin eyebrows.\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">Is It Safe?</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">While prescription\r\neyelash enhancers are often formulated with prostaglandin, a hormone that can\r\ncause side effects such as darkened irises (potentially irreversible) and\r\nblurred vision, more and more companies are developing safer, non-prescription\r\nalternatives that deliver impressive results.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">Most non-prescription\r\nformulas are hormone and paraben-free. &nbsp;Instead, they&acute;re formulated with\r\npolypeptides, amino acids, and conditioning ingredients to help rejuvenate\r\nlashes and strengthen them against breakage.&nbsp; So, you still get longer,\r\nfuller, darker-looking lashes and shapelier brows, without the negative side\r\neffects.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">How Soon Can You See\r\nResults?</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;\r\ncolor:#222222\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">In some cases, users\r\nhave reported seeing results in as little as seven days, while others may see\r\nresults in four weeks.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 16.5pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#222222\">SmartLash, for\r\ninstance, has published its clinical results, which show that 46 percent of\r\nparticipants saw a difference in their eyelashes and/or brows in just seven\r\ndays, while 100 percent saw a difference in 14 days.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-11-26 11:53:17','smallCONT-00130Test.jpg','midCONT-00130Test.jpg','bigCONT-00130Test.jpg','USR-000001','2013-11-30 01:00:11','USR-000001',4),('CONT-00131',NULL,'Kacci Biryani(ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¾ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â§Ãƒâ€šÃ‚ÂÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡',' the most yammy dish','<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: large;\"><b>Ingredients:</b></span><br>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\"><li>Mutton-1 kg</li><li>Bashmati rice- 1/2 kg</li><li>Potato(cut in cube) - 3 medium size(around 250gm)</li><li>Onion - 1 cup(chopped)</li><li>Yogurt - 1 cup</li><li>Milk- 1 cup</li><li>Cinnamon stick -4 pieces</li><li>Cardamom-5-6 pieces</li><li>Clove-3-4 pieces</li><li>Bay leaf- 4 pieces</li><li>Garlic paste-1 and 1/2 Tbs</li><li>Ginger paste- 1 and 1/2 Tbs</li><li>Garam masala powder- 1 ts</li><li>Cumin powder- 1 ts</li><li>Red chili&nbsp;powder- 1 ts</li><li>Black pepper powder- 1 ts</li><li>Nutmeg powder&nbsp;(Jaifol)- 1/2 ts</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.25em; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-indent: 0px;\">Mace powder (jaiotri)- 1/2 ts</li><li>Aloobukhara/Dried prune-7-8 pieces</li><li>Raisin -10 pieces</li><li>Keora water-1/2 Tbs</li><li>Sugar-1 ts</li><li>Ghee- 1/2 cup</li><li>Oil- 2 Tbs</li><li>Salt- 2 Tbs or according to your taste</li></ol>\r\n<div>\r\n<b><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: large;\">Procedure:</span></b></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\"><li>Clean and wash the mutton properly and keep them on a strainer to drain the excess water.</li><li>Now take the mutton in the pan (<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: blue;\">try to use an ovenproof &nbsp;heavy pan with heavy lid</span>),\r\n add yogurt, salt, sugar, half of the ghee, ginger paste, garlic paste, \r\nwhole masala (cinnamon, cardamom, clove, bay leaf) and all powder \r\nmasala. Mix all these things well with&nbsp;mutton,&nbsp;cover it and keep it \r\naside to marinate for around 2-3 hour.</li><li>In the mean time fry the potatoes lightly in oil and keep it aside. \r\nThen fry the chopped onion till it get nice golden color and take them \r\nout on a paper towel to soak extra oil and keep aside.<br>\r\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">\r\n<a href=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-I8O-Dtp4DPw/TuGF5Fc01EI/AAAAAAAABaU/6kBPz_kSWHg/s1600/kacci+biryani.jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-I8O-Dtp4DPw/TuGF5Fc01EI/AAAAAAAABaU/6kBPz_kSWHg/s400/kacci+biryani.jpg\" border=\"0\" width=\"400\" height=\"177\"></a></div>\r\n</li><li>Wash rice and cook it half and drain through a strainer to drain water.</li><li>Now add milk on the top of the mutton and then spread the rice on \r\nit.Then spread the fried potatoes , fried onion, rest of the ghee, \r\naloobukhara/Dried prune, raisin, keora water one by one on the top.<br>\r\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">\r\n<a href=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-dmppskpgrNI/TuGF53Vrt7I/AAAAAAAABac/un88as1BTW8/s1600/kacci+biryani1.jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-dmppskpgrNI/TuGF53Vrt7I/AAAAAAAABac/un88as1BTW8/s400/kacci+biryani1.jpg\" border=\"0\" width=\"400\" height=\"166\"></a></div>\r\n</li><li>Then cover the pan with lid. If the lid is not tight enough, seal the edge with flour dough.</li><li>Now preheat the oven to 375 degree F. Then put the pan in the oven \r\nand bake it around 20 minutes and then &nbsp;reduce the heat to 350 degree F \r\nand bake it around 45-50 minutes.</li><li>Then turn off the oven and leave it for around 30 minutes.</li><li>Now carefully open the lid and slowly mix the biryani from the \r\nbottom to top to make an even mix of mutton and rice in the biryani.</li><li>Serve your biryani hot and enjoy.</li></ol>\r\n</div>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-01 09:49:40','smallCONT-00131kacci_biryani.jpg','midCONT-00131kacci_biryani.jpg','bigCONT-00131kacci_biryani.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:07:20','USR-000001',1),('CONT-00132',NULL,'Cheese Fondue','Enjoy the cheesiness in every bite with the melted cheese fondue served with vegetables like broccoli and baby corn. ','Fondue is a Swiss dish made with melted cheese. For all the cheese lover, Emmenthaler and Gruyere cheese melted and drizzled with some white wine. Dip blanched vegetables like broccoli and baby corn in this hot mixture and enjoy the cheesiness in every bite.<br><div class=\"ingredient-cont\">\r\n                        <h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n                        <ul><li class=\"ingredient\">100 gm Swiss-style cheese such as Emmenthaler, shredded <br>\r\n<br>100 gm Gruyere cheese, shredded <br>\r\n<br>2 Tbsp corn flour<br>\r\n<br>1 cup dry white wine (such as Sauvignon Blanc)<br>\r\n<br>1 Tbsp lemon juice <br>\r\n<br>1/2 tsp dry mustard <br>\r\n<br>Pinch of freshly grated nutmeg <br>\r\n<br>1 broccoli, chopped<br>\r\n<br>6 baby Corn, chopped </li></ul>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                        <h3>Method</h3>\r\n                        Mix the cornstarch and the shredded cheese in a bowl. Set aside in the fridge.<br><br>Chop broccoli and baby corn, blanch them in hot water and transfer them into ice water. <br><br>Add\r\n the wine and lemon juice to the pot, and bring to a low simmer on \r\nmedium heat. Bit by bit, slowly stir the cheese into the wine. Stir \r\nconstantly in a figure of eight pattern. <br><br>Please make sure that the mixture does not boil by regulating the temperature. Cook just until the cheese is melted and creamy. <br><br>Once the mixture is smooth add the grain mustard and grated nutmeg. Keep stirring.<br><br>Transfer\r\n the cheese to a fondue serving pot, set over a low flame to keep warm. \r\nIf your pot is thin-bottomed, a lit candle will probably do. <br><br>If thick-bottomed, you can use a small Sterno.<br><br>Serve with bread and vegetable. <br>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-01 09:52:40','smallCONT-00132cheese-fondue_med.jpg','midCONT-00132cheese-fondue_med.jpg','bigCONT-00132cheese-fondue_med.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:11:40','USR-000001',5),('CONT-00133',NULL,'4 Ways to Cheer Up a Kindergartner','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n15.6pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt; line-height: 15.6pt;\">They might seem too\r\nyoung to have a lot of problems, but kindergartners can get stressed. When\r\nthings don&acute;t work out, they&acute;re not happy. It&acute;ll usually be about friends and\r\nschool.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">It&acute;s tempting to treat\r\nsadness with ice cream or cookies, TV time, or video games. But there are\r\nbetter ways to turn frowns into smiles.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">\"You don&acute;t want to\r\nbuy your kid&acute;s happiness. You want to give them skills that will help them\r\novercome sadness or anger,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â says Kristy vanMarle, PhD, assistant professor of\r\npsychological sciences at the University of Missouri ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Columbia. \"You\r\ndon&acute;t want to create kids who go to the icebox to deal with the letdowns in\r\nlife.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Doing that can lead to\r\nunhealthy weight gain and a lifetime of emotional eating.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Try these healthy\r\nsolutions instead:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">1. Play together.</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">When your child is upset about an unkind friend\r\nat school, spend time with them. \"Kids really thrive on having sensitive,\r\ncaring attention from their parents,\" says vanMarle. It lets them know\r\nthat they&acute;re loved and special.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">One of the best ways to\r\nplay is by doing something active. Take a walk or ride bikes together. Teach\r\nthem that exercise curbs stress and feels good.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">2. Talk it out.</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Kids this age often have a tough time putting\r\nwords to their feelings. They might not be able to tell you they&acute;re\r\n\"disappointed\" or \"frustrated.\" They just know they&acute;re not\r\nhappy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">You may have to help\r\nthem express their feelings. Try: \"It sounds like you&acute;re sad because\r\nMorgan wouldn&acute;t sit with you at lunch.\" Or, \"I bet it hurt your\r\nfeelings when Zach didn&acute;t pick you to be his partner.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">\"As parents, it&acute;s\r\nimportant to not trivialize your children&acute;s emotions,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â she says. ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“If kids are\r\nsaying they&acute;re sad or afraid or mad, it&acute;s critical to sit down and talk about\r\nit. It validates their feelings and makes them realize they have support.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Then, talk about what\r\nyour child can do to feel better in that situation next time, like sit or play\r\nwith someone else. Then let them know how they can feel better right now:\r\n\"Let&acute;s go for a walk together.\" Teach them that moving their body can\r\nhelp them feel better.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">The key is to listen and\r\nempathize, says vanMarle.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:9.0pt;line-height:15.6pt;background:\r\nwhite\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">3. Give them alone time.</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Kids are so used to the noise of electronics,\r\nplaying, and other kids, that sometimes a little quiet is a welcome break. It\r\nmay help them relax and calm down. After you talk, consider letting them have\r\nsome quiet time. Kids shouldn&acute;t get more than 2 hours a day of TV, computer, or\r\nvideo games combined. Too much screen time keeps kids inactive when they could\r\nbe moving and playing.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:9.0pt;margin-left:0in;\r\nline-height:15.6pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Quiet time to play by themselves can help\r\nthem learn how to be self-reliant, so they don&acute;t depend on others to keep them\r\nentertained or relax.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 9pt; line-height: 15.6pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">\"It&acute;s important for kids to be able to sit quietly once in a\r\nwhile without having input, without having instruction,\" vanMarle says.\r\n\"That&acute;s a skill that you need to develop.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 9pt; line-height: 15.6pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">4. Get them to bed.</span></b><span class=\"apple-converted-space\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Sometimes\r\nkids are cranky or don&acute;t feel well because they&acute;re tired. School-age kids ages\r\n5 to 12 need 10 to 11 hours of sleep a night.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 9pt; line-height: 15.6pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">To make sure they get it regularly, set up a calming bedtime\r\nroutine. Try a short talk about their day, a bath, and then read a book\r\ntogether. In their room, keep the lights low and the room temperature\r\ncomfortable for sleep. Have them go to bed and get up at the same time every\r\nday.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 9pt; line-height: 15.6pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Teach them that their body needs to sleep so they have the energy\r\nto play and have fun.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 9pt; line-height: 15.6pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">The good news is that kids this age easily bounce back when\r\nthey&acute;re unhappy, says vanMarle.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 9pt; line-height: 15.6pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">\"As long as you&acute;re doing things sort of normally and being a\r\nsensitive caregiver -- giving them a lot of attention when they need it, and\r\nlove, of course, all the time -- they should be fine.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-04 07:48:40','smallCONT-00133Draft 2, 4 Ways to Cheer Up a Kindergartner.jpg','midCONT-00133Draft 2, 4 Ways to Cheer Up a Kindergartner.jpg','bigCONT-00133Draft 2, 4 Ways to Cheer Up a Kindergartner.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00135',NULL,'How to Break Up With Someone','When you first started dating, you were so into your boyfriend/girlfriend. Now youÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¾Ã‚Â¢re just not feeling it anymore. ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:14.25pt;mso-outline-level:3;background:\r\nwhite\"><b style=\"line-height: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">It&acute;s over. Here&acute;s advice\r\nfor teens on how to break the news.</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:5;background:\r\nwhite\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-bidi-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#90af17;display:none;mso-hide:=\"\" all;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Why do I need to register or sign in for WebMD to\r\nsave?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; display: none;\" lang=\"EN\">We\r\nwill provide you with a dropdown of all your saved articles when you are\r\nregistered and signed in.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">When you first started\r\ndating, you were </span><i style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">so</i><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\"> into your boyfriend/girlfriend. Now you&acute;re just not\r\nfeeling it anymore. You want out.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">How do you break up without\r\nmaking someone miserable -- or making them hate you forever?<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Don&acute;t <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/balance/stress-management/\">stress</a> -- that&acute;s not\r\ngood for you. But first, here&acute;s what NOT to do:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Don&acute;t tell your friends before you break up. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Don&acute;t post it on Facebook. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Don&acute;t text or email it. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Here&acute;s why.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#705e3e;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Don&acute;t Text the Bad News<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">You may be tempted to text\r\na breakup to avoid arguments and tears. But don&acute;t go there.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#737373;display:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:=\"\" en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">When it comes to breaking\r\nup, \"text messages suck,\" says Annie Fox, MEd, author of <i>The Teen\r\nSurvival Guide to Dating and Relating</i>. \"It&acute;s cold and it&acute;s\r\nunnecessarily disrespectful.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">But many <a href=\"http://children.webmd.com/tc/growth-and-development-ages-15-to-18-years-promoting-healthy-growth-and-development\">teens</a>\r\ndo it. In a survey, 30% of 13-to-17-year-olds said they&acute;d either broken up\r\nwith, or been dumped by, someone via text message.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Changing your Facebook\r\nstatus from \"In a relationship\" to \"Single\" is also not the\r\nway to tell your boyfriend or girlfriend you&acute;re through.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">If you post it,\r\n\"everybody gets to comment, and you&acute;re bringing everybody into your world,\"\r\nsays teen <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/mental-health/guide-to-psychiatry-and-counseling\">psychologist</a>\r\nJennifer Hartstein, PsyD.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Instead, think about how\r\nyou&acute;d want someone to break up with you, and try to do the same thing.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#705e3e;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">The <st1:street w:st=\"on\"><st1:address w:st=\"on\">Best Way</st1:address></st1:street> to Break Up<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Ask yourself why you want\r\nto end the relationship. \"You really need to know why you&acute;re doing\r\nthis,\" Fox says. \"Because if someone is breaking up with you, the\r\nfirst question you always ask is, &acute;Why? Did I do something wrong?&acute;\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">If you&acute;ve started to like someone\r\nelse, that&acute;s OK. Or if you just don&acute;t feel the same way you used to, that&acute;s\r\nfine, too.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">You can&acute;t blame yourself\r\nfor falling out of love. But still, don&acute;t be mean. Make sure you treat the\r\nother person with respect.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">If the person you&acute;re dating\r\nhasn&acute;t respected your feelings -- or worse, has been aggressive or violent --\r\nyou have more than enough reason for wanting out.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#705e3e;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Do It in Person<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Once you know why you want\r\nto end the relationship, \"Be honest with yourself. And then be honest when\r\nyou talk with them -- privately, face-to-face,\" Fox says.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Know that no matter how\r\ngently you handle the breakup, you&acute;re going to hurt the other person&acute;s\r\nfeelings, Hartstein says. That&acute;s something you need to accept.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">\"When you say, &acute;I\r\ndon&acute;t want to be with you anymore,&acute; you know before you say it -- if you have a\r\nheart -- that you&acute;re going to be hurting someone. You also know that you&acute;d\r\nnever want to be on the receiving end of what you&acute;re about to dish out,\"\r\nFox says.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#705e3e;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Make It Stick<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Even if you can&acute;t stand the\r\nsight of your ex crying, don&acute;t back down.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 05:20:41','smallCONT-00135Article - 01, 69x75_how_to_break_up_with_someone_features.jpg','midCONT-00135Article - 01, 69x75_how_to_break_up_with_someone_features.jpg','bigCONT-00135Article - 01, 69x75_how_to_break_up_with_someone_features.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:12:28','USR-000001',2),('CONT-00136',NULL,'How to Tell if Someone Likes You','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:14.25pt;mso-outline-level:3;background:\r\nwhite\"><b style=\"line-height: 12pt;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">You like them, but do they\r\nlike you back? Here are clues.</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">When you like\r\nsomeone, it can be tough to tell if they like you back. But if you&acute;re ever\r\ngoing to get together, you have to start somewhere.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Figuring out if\r\nsomeone likes you is the first step toward a healthy relationship. So here&acute;s\r\nhow to do that<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Hint: It&acute;s all about\r\nhealthy self-esteem for yourself and respect for the other person.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#705e3e;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\">Ask the Right Question\r\nFirst<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Instead of wondering\r\nif someone likes you, you should first ask yourself if you really like <i>them</i>,\r\nsays psychotherapist Elsbeth Martindale, PsyD.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Her advice: Take it\r\nslow. Check out the person&acute;s values -- do they match yours?<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Look for someone who\r\nmatches you,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â Martindale says. She wrote a book called <i>Things to Know Before\r\nYou say \"Go\"</i> for her teen clients who were getting their &acute;hearts\r\nstomped on,\" she says.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Remember, this should\r\nbe fun. If you&acute;re not having fun -- and more importantly, if you&acute;re not feeling\r\ngood about yourself with someone -- then walk away.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">You may be much\r\nhappier on your own! There is nothing wrong with being single, even if everyone\r\nelse seems to be coupling up. It can be your healthiest, most fun option.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#705e3e;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\">Clues, Good and Bad<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">What if you really do\r\nlike that person and you&acute;re trying to figure out if they like you back?<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">\"Trust your\r\ngut,\" says <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Didi Zahariades</st1:city>, <st1:state w:st=\"on\">MA</st1:state>, a teen life coach in <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Portland</st1:city>, <st1:state w:st=\"on\">Ore.</st1:state></st1:place><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Don&acute;t overthink it.\r\nDon&acute;t spend too much time counting how many times she looked at you during\r\nclass or what his text that just said ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Hey,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â might mean.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“If you&acute;re spending a\r\nlot of time trying to figure out if this person likes you or doesn&acute;t, then he\r\nprobably doesn&acute;t,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â Zahariades says.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Instead, consider\r\nthis:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Often or not? </span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">How often do you hear from\r\nthem? Does she always wait for you after calculus or grab the seat next to you\r\nat lunch? If they&acute;re consistently showing you attention, you&acute;re hearing from\r\nthem often, \"that may mean something,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â Zahariades says. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Focused or scattered?</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"> Does he stand and talk\r\nwith you for more than a minute or so in the hall? Does she stay there even\r\nwhen her best friends pass by? If she keeps hanging out with you, that may mean\r\nsomething. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Eye contact.</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"> This one can go both ways.\r\nIf someone makes a lot of eye contact with you, that can be a good sign. But\r\nsome people who are really shy find it tough to make eye contact, so you can&acute;t\r\nbe sure about that. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Getting personal.</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"> What do they talk to you\r\nabout? Are they asking about what&acute;s going on with you -- your classes, your\r\nafter-school job, or your plans after graduation? Are they hinting at getting\r\ntogether by asking about what you&acute;re doing this weekend?&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 05:35:50','smallCONT-00136Article - 02, 69x75_does_she_he_like_me_features.jpg','midCONT-00136Article - 02, 69x75_does_she_he_like_me_features.jpg','bigCONT-00136Article - 02, 69x75_does_she_he_like_me_features.jpg','USR-000001','2013-12-31 02:50:48','USR-000001',13),('CONT-00137',NULL,'Guide to Gluten-Free Flours','What to know about gluten-free flours, including nutritional information.','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:14.25pt;mso-outline-level:3;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"color: red; line-height: 12pt;\">What to know about gluten-free flours,\r\nincluding nutritional information.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Are you on a\r\ngluten-free diet? Regular breads, bagels, muffins, and many other store-bought\r\nbaked goods are not allowed on gluten-free eating plans. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\">Here&acute;s what you need to know before you buy\r\ngluten-free grain products or bake them at home.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#705e3e;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">What Is Gluten?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Gluten is a protein\r\npresent in wheat flour, which is widely used in commercial and homemade baked\r\ngoods. Gluten is also found in flour made from barley, rye, spelt, and\r\ntriticale, a cross between wheat and rye. Gluten helps dough to rise and lends\r\nshape and a chewy texture to baked goods.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">\"Baking without\r\ngluten can be challenging because gluten contributes important properties to\r\nbaked products like cookies, cakes, pastries, and breads,\" says Carol\r\nFenster, PhD, author of 10 gluten-free cookbooks, including <i>1,000\r\nGluten-Free Recipes</i>, and her most recent, <i>125 Gluten-Free Vegetarian\r\nRecipes</i>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">That&acute;s why, in\r\naddition to seeing gluten-free flours such as white rice flour listed in the\r\ningredient list, you may also notice xanthan gum and guar gum. \"These gums\r\nwork with other ingredients, such as yeast, baking soda, and baking powder, to\r\nhelp the dough or batter rise,\" Fenster says.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#705e3e;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Read the Label<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">For the estimated 3\r\nmillion Americans with celiac disease, avoiding gluten is a must for good\r\nhealth. Others avoid gluten because they feel sensitive to it.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#737373;display:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:=\"\" en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Among some people\r\nwith celiac disease and gluten intolerance, gluten-free goods may have a\r\n\"health halo.\" That is, they&acute;re considered more nutritionally\r\nvaluable for what they contain -- or don&acute;t contain, in the case of gluten.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Gluten-free bread,\r\nbagels, and muffins may taste better now than when they first hit store shelves\r\nyears ago, but they haven&acute;t improved much nutritionally.&nbsp;The store-bought\r\ngluten-free baked goods you eat on a regular basis, such as bread and bagels,\r\nare not created equal to regular varieties made with wheat flour.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Wheat flour is\r\ntypically enriched with vitamins and minerals, including iron, <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/drugs/drug-8334-Folic+Acid+Oral.aspx?drugid=8334&amp;drugname=Folic+Acid+Oral\">folic\r\nacid</a>, and other B vitamins, and whole wheat flour supplies fiber. You can&acute;t\r\ncount on gluten-free flours to provide the same nutrient profile.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">It&acute;s important to\r\nread the Nutrient Facts panels carefully to help avoid certain nutrient\r\nshortfalls on a gluten-free eating plan.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">\"Purchase\r\ngluten-free products with added vitamins and minerals, and look for items made\r\nwith whole grain flour or bean flour to help you get the nutrients you\r\nneed,\" says Shelley Case, RD, nutrition consultant and author of <i>Gluten-Free\r\nDiet: A Comprehensive Resource Guide</i>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Although there&acute;s no\r\nshortage of refined carbohydrates in most commercial gluten-free baked goods,\r\nmost are lower in fiber, Case says.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">\"When there&acute;s no\r\ngluten in a recipe, it takes far more gluten-free ingredients to produce a\r\ntasty product,\" Case explains.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">The refined\r\ncarbohydrates typically used in gluten-free products and mixes, including white\r\nrice flour and tapioca, produce baked goods that are much higher in calories\r\nand total carbohydrates than regular versions.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Simply swapping\r\nregular bread, muffins, and other baked items for gluten-free products without\r\nany regard for calories can easily lead to <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/diet/old-diet-toc\">weight gain</a>. Case warns that\r\ngluten-free baked goods won&acute;t necessarily help you with <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/diet/default.htm\">weight control</a>, and they may\r\nhinder <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/diet/tc/healthy-weight-what-is-a-healthy-weight\">weight</a>\r\ncontrol efforts.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;, serif;\" lang=\"EN\">Gluten-free or not, it\r\nalways pays to be aware of your personal calorie budget for weight\r\ncontrol.&nbsp;Check the calories and serving sizes of store-bought baked goods,\r\nand make sure all the foods you eat, including gluten-free cookies, cake, and\r\nbrownies, fit into your daily calorie allowance for weight maintenance or\r\nweight loss.</span>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 05:37:03','smallCONT-00137Article - 03, 110x70_gluten_free_flours_features.jpg','midCONT-00137Article - 03, 110x70_gluten_free_flours_features.jpg','bigCONT-00137Article - 03, 110x70_gluten_free_flours_features.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:10:43','USR-000001',6),('CONT-00138',NULL,'Caffeine Myths and Facts','Chances are you have some real misperceptions about caffeine','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 12pt;\">Caffeine myth or\r\ncaffeine fact? It&acute;s not always easy to know. Chances are you have some real\r\nmisperceptions about caffeine. For starters, do you know the most common\r\nsources of caffeine? Well, maybe two of the sources aren&acute;t too hard to name --\r\ncoffee and tea leaves. But did you know kola nuts and cocoa beans are also\r\nincluded among the most common caffeine sources? And do you know how much\r\ncaffeine content can vary from food to food? Turns out it&acute;s quite a lot\r\nactually, depending on the type and serving size of a food or beverage and how\r\nit&acute;s prepared.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Caffeine content can\r\nrange from as much as 160 milligrams in some energy drinks to as little as 4\r\nmilligrams in a 1-ounce serving of chocolate-flavored syrup. Even decaffeinated\r\ncoffee isn&acute;t completely free of caffeine. Caffeine is also present in some\r\nover-the-counter pain relievers, cold medications, and diet pills. These\r\nproducts can contain as little as 16 milligrams or as much as 200 milligrams of\r\ncaffeine. In fact, caffeine itself is a mild painkiller and increases the\r\neffectiveness of other pain relievers.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Want to know more?\r\nRead on. WebMD has examined some of the most common myths about caffeine and\r\ngathered the facts to shed some light on those myths.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:red;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Caffeine Myth No. 1: Caffeine\r\nIs Addictive<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">This one has some\r\ntruth to it, depending on what you mean by \"addictive.\" Caffeine is a\r\nstimulant to the central nervous system, and regular use of caffeine does cause\r\nmild physical dependence. But caffeine doesn&acute;t threaten your physical, social,\r\nor economic health the way addictive drugs do. (Although after seeing your\r\nmonthly spending at the coffee shop, you might disagree!)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">If you stop taking\r\ncaffeine abruptly, you may have symptoms for a day or more, especially if you\r\nconsume two or more cups of coffee a day. Symptoms of withdrawal from caffeine\r\ninclude:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">headache <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">fatigue <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">anxiety <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">irritability <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">depressed mood <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">difficulty concentrating <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#737373;display:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:=\"\" en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">No doubt, caffeine\r\nwithdrawal can make for a few bad days. However, caffeine does not cause the\r\nseverity of withdrawal or harmful drug-seeking behaviors as street drugs or\r\nalcohol. For this reason, most experts don&acute;t consider caffeine dependence a\r\nserious addiction.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:15.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:4;background:white\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-bidi-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#799a41;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Caffeine Myth No. 2:\r\nCaffeine Is Likely to Cause Insomnia<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Your body quickly\r\nabsorbs caffeine. But it also gets rid of it quickly. Processed mainly through\r\nthe liver, caffeine has a relatively short half-life. This means it takes about\r\nfive to seven hours, on average, to eliminate half of it from your body. After\r\neight to 10 hours, 75% of the caffeine is gone. For most people, a cup of\r\ncoffee or two in the morning won&acute;t interfere with sleep at night.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">Consuming caffeine\r\nlater in the day, however, <i>can</i> interfere with sleep. If you&acute;re like most\r\npeople, your sleep won&acute;t be affected if you don&acute;t consume caffeine at least six\r\nhours before going to bed. Your sensitivity may vary, though, depending on your\r\nmetabolism and the amount of caffeine you regularly consume. People who are\r\nmore sensitive may not only experience insomnia but also have caffeine side\r\neffects of nervousness and gastrointestinal upset.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 05:39:56','smallCONT-00138Article - 04, 110x70_caffeine.jpg','midCONT-00138Article - 04, 110x70_caffeine.jpg','bigCONT-00138Article - 04, 110x70_caffeine.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:09:47','USR-000001',11),('CONT-00139',NULL,'Alkaline Diet: What to Know Before Trying It',' Potential Risks and Benefits of the Alkaline Diet','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15pt; background-color: white; line-height: 16.5pt;\">Potential Risks and Benefits of the Alkaline Diet</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9.5pt; background-color: white; line-height: 12pt;\">By Sonya Collins</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Reviewed by </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/louise-chang\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Louise Chang, MD</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Trying\r\nout the latest diet is practically an American pastime. The more health\r\nbenefits the diet supposedly provides, the better. We don&acute;t just want to </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/diet/old-diet-toc\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">lose weight</a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">; we want to cure </span><a href=\"http://arthritis.webmd.com/default.htm\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">arthritis</a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, </span><a href=\"http://diabetes.webmd.com/default.htm\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">diabetes</a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, and </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cancer/\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">cancer</a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, and slow the aging process,\r\ntoo. Some web sites touting the alkaline diet claim it does all these things\r\nand more.</span></p><div><img src=\"adminppl/contentimage/12Eat Fresh.jpg\" alt=\"\" alignment=\"\" border=\"\" vspace=\"\" hspace=\"\"></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Is\r\nit true? Here&acute;s what you need to know.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">First,\r\nsome background information. Our pH is the measure of exactly how acidic or\r\nalkaline we are. A pH of 0 is completely acidic, and a pH of 14 completely\r\nalkaline. A pH of 7 is neutral.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">You\r\ndon&acute;t just have one pH level. For example, the <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/digestive-disorders/picture-of-the-stomach\">stomach</a>\r\nhas a pH ranging from 1.35-3.5. It must be acidic to aid in digestion. However,\r\nblood must always be slightly alkaline, with a pH of 7.35 to 7.45.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">The\r\ntheory of the alkaline diet is that eating certain foods can help maintain the\r\nbody&acute;s ideal pH balance to improve overall health. But the body maintains its\r\npH balance regardless of diet.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">For\r\ninstance, your diet may affect the pH level of your urine. <span style=\"background:white\">But what you eat does not determine your blood&acute;s pH\r\nlevel.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";color:#737373;=\"\" display:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:=\"\" en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">What&acute;s in the Alkaline Diet<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">The\r\nalkaline diet is mostly vegetarian. In addition to fresh vegetables and some\r\nfresh fruits, alkaline-promoting foods include soy products and some nuts,\r\ngrains, and legumes.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Web\r\nsites promoting the alkaline diet discourage eating acid-promoting foods, which\r\ninclude meat, fish, poultry, dairy products, processed foods, white sugar,\r\nwhite flour, and <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/balance/caffeine-myths-and-facts\">caffeine</a>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">The\r\nalkaline diet is basically healthy, says Marjorie Nolan, RD, an American\r\nDietetic Association spokeswoman.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\"It&acute;s\r\na diet of fresh <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/food-recipes/features/fruits-veggies-more-matters\">fruits\r\nand vegetables</a>, plenty of water, avoiding processed foods, coffee, and\r\nalcohol, which are all recommendations for a generally healthy diet\r\nanyway,\" Nolan says. \"But our body regulates our pH between 7.35 and\r\n7.45 no matter how we eat.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:=\"\" en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Potential Benefits<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Diets\r\nthat include a lot of animal protein can lower urine pH and raise the risk for <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/kidney-stones/default.htm\">kidney stones</a>. So\r\neating a diet rich in vegetables, as with an alkaline diet, can raise urine pH\r\nand lower the risk for kidney stones, says John Asplin, MD, a kidney specialist\r\nwho is a fellow of the American Society of Nephrology.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Researchers\r\nhave speculated that an alkaline diet might slow bone loss and muscle waste,\r\nincrease growth hormone, make certain chronic diseases less likely, and ease\r\nlow <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/back-pain/default.htm\">back pain</a>.\r\nHowever, that hasn&acute;t been proven.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">There\r\nis also no concrete evidence that an alkaline or </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/food-recipes/guide/vegetarian-and-vegan-diet\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">vegetarian\r\ndiet</a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> can prevent cancer. Some studies have shown that vegetarians have\r\nlower rates of cancer, particularly </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/colorectal-cancer/default.htm\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">colon cancer</a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">,\r\naccording to the American Cancer Society. But vegetarians often have other\r\nhealthy habits, such as </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/fitness-exercise/guide/default.htm\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">exercise</a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> and\r\nabstaining from drinking and smoking, so it is difficult to determine the\r\neffects of diet alone.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\"Clinical\r\nstudies have proved without a doubt that people who eat more fresh fruits and\r\nvegetables and hydrate properly do have lower rates of cancer and other\r\ndiseases,\" Nolan tells WebMD, \"but it probably has nothing to do with\r\nblood pH.\"</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 05:42:05','smallCONT-00139Draft 04, 110x70_alkaline_diets_what_to_know_features[1].jpg','midCONT-00139Draft 04, 110x70_alkaline_diets_what_to_know_features[1].jpg','bigCONT-00139Draft 04, 110x70_alkaline_diets_what_to_know_features[1].jpg','USR-000001','2013-12-28 03:44:07','USR-000001',9),('CONT-00140',NULL,'Spring Vegetable Guide','Italians have a deep attachment to the artichoke','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15pt; background-color: white; line-height: 16.5pt;\">How to choose the best vegetables for the spring season.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Spring-fresh and\r\nnutrient-packed artichokes, asparagus, peas and salad greens are in season now.\r\nThis handy guide offers information on picking the best spring vegetables and\r\nthe health benefits of each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;\">Artichokes</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Italians\r\nhave a deep attachment to the artichoke, which is native to the Mediterranean\r\nand first appeared in modern records in Naples around 1400. When spring rolls\r\naround in Rome, artichokes are served every way possible, from deep-fried to\r\nthinly sliced raw and topped with shaved pecorino and fruity olive oil. Then\r\nwhen the season is over, frozen and canned artichokes are definitely\r\nconvenient, making artichokes a great addition to weeknight meals and quick\r\ndips.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> Plenty of fiber and a good amount of vitamin C, potassium and folate make\r\nartichokes an obvious healthy choice.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Shopping\r\nTip:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nLook for green, plump, compact heads. Brown spots on the scales may be\r\nunattractive but indicate that the artichokes have been frost-kissed and have\r\nimproved flavor.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Storage\r\nTip:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nRefrigerate in a plastic bag for up to 1 week.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\r\n\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Asparagus<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">King\r\nLouis XIV of France was so fond of asparagus he ordered greenhouses to grow the\r\ndelicacy year-round. Today, you don&acute;t need to be royalty to enjoy it anytime,\r\nbut it is the freshest and tastiest in spring.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";color:#737373;=\"\" display:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> One stalk of asparagus contains just 4 calories and delivers healthy doses\r\nof folate, potassium and fiber.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Shopping\r\nTips:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nConsumers who choose spindly asparagus are actually missing the juicy\r\ntenderness of fatter, more robust spears. \"Elegantly thin\" asparagus\r\nis less sweet, more grassy and herbaceous. Shun any spear that appears\r\nshriveled or whose bud is spreading open.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Storage\r\nTip:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\"> If\r\nyou&acute;re not going to eat your asparagus within a day or two, stand it upright in\r\na glass of water to keep it hydrated.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\r\n\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Peas<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Only\r\nabout 5 percent of the peas grown in the world are actually eaten freshÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âmost\r\nare frozen or canned. Do your part to boost the statistics by indulging in\r\nfresh spring peasÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âsnap, snow or English shelling. Choose snow peas or snap peas\r\nif you&acute;re looking for the tasty edible pods to throw in a salad or to simply\r\nsautÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â© and choose shelling varieties for the fun-to-open pods full of little\r\ngreen gems.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> Bursting with nutrients, peas are a very good source of vitamin K,\r\nmanganese, vitamin C, iron, fiber, vitamin B1 and folate, as well as a good\r\nsource of a host of other vitamins and minerals.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Shopping\r\nTip:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nLook for peas with light, bright coloring without any brown, bruised, withering\r\nends.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Storage\r\nTip:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nRefrigerate peas for 2 to 4 days.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\r\n\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Salad Greens<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Salads\r\nusing fresh, seasonal greens are an ideal way to get dinner on the table fast\r\nwithout spending much time in front of the stove. Sandwiches are good places\r\nfor greens too: try watercress on a tuna salad sandwich or arugula on a grilled\r\nvegetable sandwich.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 05:44:06','smallCONT-00140Draft 05, 300x310_spring_vegetable_guide[1].jpg','midCONT-00140Draft 05, 300x310_spring_vegetable_guide[1].jpg','bigCONT-00140Draft 05, 300x310_spring_vegetable_guide[1].jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:08:06','USR-000001',4),('CONT-00141',NULL,'Nutty About Peanut Butter','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15pt; background-color: white; line-height: 16.5pt;\">Shopping, eating, and cooking tips for peanut butter, an\r\nall-American favorite.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; font-size: 10pt;\">As\r\nAmerican as apple pie, peanut butter has made its mark on American cuisine\r\nsince the early 1900s. Whether it&acute;s partnering with jelly on bread or is the\r\nfeatured ingredient in cookie dough, it&acute;s an enduring favorite. Most households\r\nhave a jar of it in the kitchen at all times.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">But\r\nis peanut butter good for you? Well, like most nut butters, peanut butter is\r\nhigh in fat and calories (with around 190 calories and 16 grams of fat per 2\r\ntablespoons). But the good news is, you get a lot of <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/diet/old-diet-toc\">nutrition</a> for your\r\n190-calorie investment. Nuts and nut butters are a great source of protein,\r\nfiber, <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/vitamins-and-supplements/vitamins-and-their-functions-and-sources\">vitamins</a>,\r\nminerals, and phytochemicals.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">In\r\n2003 the FDA approved a qualified health claim for peanuts and certain tree\r\nnuts. It basically says that scientific evidence suggests that eating 1.5\r\nounces per day of most nuts (as part of a diet low in saturated fat and <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cholesterol-management/default.htm\">cholesterol</a>)\r\nmay reduce the risk of <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/heart-disease/default.htm\">heart\r\ndisease</a>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Most\r\nof the research suggesting health benefits to nuts has involved lowering the\r\nrisk of heart or cardiovascular disease or their risk factors. But there is\r\nsome evidence nuts may help with other diseases as well. For example, peanuts\r\nare a source of the phytochemical resveratrol (also found in grape skins and\r\nred wine). A recent German study explored resveratrol&acute;s possible <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cancer/\">cancer</a>-preventing effects in colorectal\r\ncells.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Acts Like a Nut <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">The\r\nfunny thing is, the peanut is actually a legume, native to South America, that\r\nhappens to look and taste like a nut.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";color:#737373;=\"\" display:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Nutritionally,\r\npeanuts act like nuts, too. About half their weight comes from fat, with the\r\nrest split fairly evenly between protein and carbohydrate (with fiber). About\r\nhalf of their total fat comes from monounsaturated fat, the kind that is linked\r\nto more healthful blood lipid levels. One-third of the fat comes from\r\npolyunsaturated fat (all of which is omega-6 fatty acid, not the superhealthy\r\nomega-3). About 14% of the fat is naturally saturated.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">What to Look for\r\nin Peanut Butter <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">When\r\nshopping for peanut butter, look for a natural style product with little to no\r\nadded fat or sugar. Some companies add partially hydrogenated oils to the\r\nregular type of peanut butter. And depending on the amount added, this could\r\nadd trans fats into the equation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">When\r\nit comes to sodium, even most natural brands of peanut butter add some salt for\r\nflavor. A little goes a long way, though. Around 120 milligrams sodium per 2\r\ntablespoons usually does the trick!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Here\r\nis a comparison of a few brands of peanut butter:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">JIF.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\"> JIF is a great-tasting peanut butter, made mostly from\r\nroasted peanuts with a little bit of sugar thrown in, along with a bit (2% or less)\r\nof molasses, partially hydrogenated soybean oil, and fully hydrogenated\r\nrapeseed and soybean oil. Each 2-tablespoon serving contains:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">190 calories\r\n<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">16 grams of\r\nfat, 3 grams of which are saturated <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">0 grams\r\ntrans fat (to make this label claim, the product must have 0.4 grams of trans\r\nfat or less per serving) <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">3 grams of\r\nsugar <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">8 grams of\r\nprotein <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\" lang=\"EN\">2 grams of\r\nfiber <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 05:54:20','smallCONT-00141Draft 01,110x70_kids_recipe_apple_slices_with_peanut_butter_ref_guide[1].jpg','midCONT-00141Draft 01,110x70_kids_recipe_apple_slices_with_peanut_butter_ref_guide[1].jpg','bigCONT-00141Draft 01,110x70_kids_recipe_apple_slices_with_peanut_butter_ref_guide[1].jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:02:18','USR-000001',7),('CONT-00142',NULL,'Understanding Digestion in Children','','<p class=\"Heading12\" style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13pt;\">Fiber-Rich Sack Lunches to Help Ease Constipation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"byline2\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; background-color: white;\">Most kids don&acute;t get enough fiber in their daily\r\ndiet -- and that can lead to a host of digestive problems, the most obvious of\r\nwhich is constipation. Fiber doesn&acute;t get digested by the human body, so it\r\nmoves through your digestive tract and cleans up the pipes -- allowing a\r\nsmoother, easier passage for waste products.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">So one of the best ways to keep your child regular\r\nand promote his digestive health is to feed him plenty of fiber. Instead of\r\nsitting him down at the counter with a big bowl of bran flakes, try these\r\ndietitian-approved, kid-friendly snacks and lunch items that will go down easy\r\nin every way.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Homemade Trail\r\nMix<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Help kids make their own trail mix by putting out\r\nbowls of dried fruit, nuts, or seeds along with a higher-fiber cereal, and\r\nmixing them up into to-go containers or plastic bags, recommends Louise\r\nGoldberg, RD, LD, owner of An Apple A Day Nutrition Consulting in Houston,\r\nTexas, and formerly a dietitian at the Children&acute;s Memorial Hermann Hospital in\r\nthe Houston Medical Center. (Just be sure to minimize the sugary ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“treatÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â\r\ningredients, like chocolate chips or other candies.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Flavorful Fruits\r\nand Veggies<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Many fruits and vegetables are high in fiber\r\n--particularly with the skin on. If your child resists them, try making them\r\nfun by spearing fruit and veggie slices onto a kebab, or making a face with\r\nsliced-up fruits and veggies, suggests Beth Pinkos, MS, RD, LDN, a dietitian\r\nfor the department of pediatric gastroenterology, hepatology, nutrition, and\r\nliver diseases at Hasbro Children&acute;s Hospital in Rhode Island.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“You can use raisins for eyes, baby carrots for a\r\nnose, and celery for eyebrows, and an apple slice for a smile,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â she says.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Remember not to give carrots to children younger\r\nthan 3 or raisins to kids younger than 4 as they can be a choking hazard.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Creamy Dips<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Kids who resist fiber-rich fruits and veggies may\r\nalso be more adventurous if they can dip them in something first -- like\r\nyogurt, peanut butter, salad dressing, or hummus.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Mixed-Up Cereals<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Having trouble getting your child to try that\r\nwhole-wheat fiber cereal? Try mixing up a couple of high-fiber cereals with a\r\nsmall amount of one of the less good-for-you options that your child may be\r\ndrawn to in the cereal aisle.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Kids like to mix and match cereals like little\r\nchemists,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â says Pinkos. ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Look for a high-fiber cereal that has 3 to 5 grams of\r\nfiber per serving, and then let them mix it up with just a little bit of one of\r\nthe junkier ones.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading37\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Sandwich in Some\r\nFiber<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Just as with cereal, the whole-grain breads or\r\nwraps you&acute;re using for your kids&acute; sandwiches should have at least three grams\r\nof fiber per serving.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"NormalWeb18\" style=\"background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:\r\n9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Check the package -- just because it&acute;s called\r\nÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¹Ã…â€œwhole grain,&acute; that doesn&acute;t always translate to fiber,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â says Goldberg. ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“And\r\ndon&acute;t be fooled by red- and green-colored wraps -- that doesn&acute;t necessarily\r\ntranslate to fiber either.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 06:00:41','smallCONT-00142Draft 08,  110x70_fiberrich_sack_lunches_features[1].jpg','midCONT-00142Draft 08,  110x70_fiberrich_sack_lunches_features[1].jpg','bigCONT-00142Draft 08,  110x70_fiberrich_sack_lunches_features[1].jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00143',NULL,'15 Healthy Foods','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15pt; background-color: white; line-height: 16.5pt;\">A grocery list to help you cut food prices while you\r\nboost nutrition</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">How\r\ndo you eat a nutritious diet while keeping your grocery bill low? The good news\r\nis that cheap eats aren&acute;t necessarily unhealthy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">You\r\ncan cut food costs by eating more meals at home and by making sure they feature\r\nsome of the healthiest foods from your supermarket -- foods like whole grains,\r\nvegetables, and beans.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";color:#737373;=\"\" display:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">1. Brown Rice<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Great\r\nfor</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">:\r\nSide dishes, rice salads, fried rice, casseroles, soups, and stews.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What&acute;s\r\na serving?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> 1/4 cup dry rice.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Nutrition\r\ninfo per serving:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> 170 calories, 2 grams fiber, and 4 grams protein.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">2. Whole-Wheat or\r\nMultigrain Pasta<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Great\r\nfor:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\"> Hot\r\nand cold pasta dishes.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What&acute;s\r\na serving?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> 2 ounces of dried pasta. A serving for most people translates into about 2\r\nounces of dried pasta, which means you get about 7 servings in the typical box\r\nor bag of dried pasta.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Nutrition\r\ninfo per serving</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\">: About 200 calories, 7 grams protein, and 6 grams fiber.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">3. 100%\r\nWhole-Wheat Bread<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Great\r\nfor:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\"> Hot\r\nand cold sandwiches, bread stuffing, bread pudding, and breakfast strata.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What&acute;s\r\na serving?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> 2 slices. Labels usually list a serving as 1 slice of bread (about 28\r\ngrams per slice), but for our purposes, we&acute;ll use the amount you&acute;d use to make\r\na sandwich.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Nutrition\r\ninfo per serving (2 slices)</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">: About 120 calories, 6 grams protein, and 3 grams fiber.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">4. Nonfat Greek\r\nYogurt<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Great\r\nfor:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\"> A\r\nquick snack, parfaits made with fruit and granola, and smoothies.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What&acute;s\r\na serving?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> Most individual servings come in 6-ounce or 8-ounce containers. You can\r\nsave money by buying a larger container of Greek yogurt and then taking your 6-\r\nor 8-ounce portion from it.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Price\r\nper serving:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> Individual servings (6- to 8-ounce containers) cost about 89 cents each\r\nand sometimes less when found on sale.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Nutrition\r\ninfo per serving</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> (for a 6-ounce serving of honey vanilla): 150 calories, 0 grams fiber, and\r\n14 grams protein.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 06:02:22','smallCONT-00143Draft 07, 110x70_cheap_and_healthy_15_nutritious_foods_for_about_2_features[1].jpg','midCONT-00143Draft 07, 110x70_cheap_and_healthy_15_nutritious_foods_for_about_2_features[1].jpg','bigCONT-00143Draft 07, 110x70_cheap_and_healthy_15_nutritious_foods_for_about_2_features[1].jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 09:11:10','USR-000001',8),('CONT-00144',NULL,'Spring Fruit Guide','How to choose the best fruit of the spring season','<p class=\"Heading25\">Delicious spring\r\nfruitÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âstrawberries, apricots, mangoes and rhubarbÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âis in the market now. This\r\nhandy guide offers information on picking the best spring fruit and the health\r\nbenefits of each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Apricots</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Before\r\npeaches, plums and berries appear in markets, apricots arrive. Ancient Romans\r\nwere so impressed by this fruit&acute;s early ripening that they took to calling it\r\npraecocium, Latin for \"precocious.\" Most apricots are destined to be\r\ncanned or dried, and their season is fleeting, so get fresh ones fast.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> Low in calories and packed with nutrients, just three fresh apricots will\r\ngive you almost half the vitamin A you need for the day along with a healthy\r\ndose of vitamin C, potassium and fiber. In addition, apricots are packed with\r\nbeta carotene, an antioxidant that helps neutralize free radicals that damage\r\ncells.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Shopping\r\nTips:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nPurchase plump, fairly firm apricots that are orange-yellow to orange. Ripe\r\napricots are soft and juicyÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âthey should be eaten as soon as possible.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Storage\r\nTips:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\"> To\r\nripen apricots, place hard fruit in a brown paper bag for one or two days. Ripe\r\napricots should be stored in the refrigerator to prevent overripening.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Fresh\r\napricots can be frozen:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\"> Just halve the fruit, remove the pit and freeze on a\r\nbaking sheet. Once frozen, place the apricots in a sealable plastic bag.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";color:#737373;=\"\" display:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Mangoes<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Mangoes\r\nhave been integrated into food cultures across the globeÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âsold fresh, as juice,\r\nin drinks, in curries and in dessertsÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âfor every meal.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> The deep orange color of mangoes comes from a high content of beta\r\ncarotene, a potent anticancer agent. Mangoes also contain vitamin C, fiber,\r\nlutein, potassium and zeaxanthin, phytochemicals known to boost the immune\r\nsystem.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Shopping\r\nTips:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nMost mangoes in U.S. grocery stores are one of five varieties: Ataulfo,\r\nFrancine, Keitt, Kent, Tommy Atkins.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Color\r\nis not an indication of ripeness, as mangoes come in many shades of green,\r\nyellow and red.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Choose\r\nmangoes with a slight \"give\" if you plan to eat them in a day or two\r\nand choose firmer mangoes for enjoying later.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Storage\r\nTips:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nUnripe mangoes will ripen at room temperature.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Refrigerate\r\nripe mangoes for up to 5 days.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Rhubarb<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Rhubarb\r\nis often called \"pie plant\" in the U.S. because it&acute;s so closely\r\nidentified with strawberry-rhubarb pie.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> Low in calories and full of fiber, potassium and vitamin C, rhubarb also\r\ncontains catechin, a flavonol that may contribute to heart health.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Shopping\r\nTip:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nLook for bright, crisp stalks with minimal pitting, dryness and other visible\r\ndamage.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Storage\r\nTips:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nRefrigerate rhubarb in a plastic bag for up to a week. Freeze diced rhubarb in\r\nan airtight container for up to 6 months.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\">Strawberries<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Few\r\nthings are closer to perfection than a strawberry when its season arrives. Even\r\nthough they&acute;re plentiful in supermarkets year-round, nothing beats the flavor\r\nof a juicy, sun-ripened strawberry in season.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\" lang=\"EN\"> Low in calories and rich in vitamin C, a 1-cup serving of strawberries\r\nprovides more than 100 percent of your daily vitamin C needs. In addition,\r\nstrawberries provide plenty of fiber, some potassium and several powerful\r\nantioxidants, such as anthocyanidin and proanthocyanidins, which promote heart\r\nhealth and may promote optimum brain functioning.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">Shopping\r\nTips:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">\r\nStrawberries do not ripen further after picking. Therefore, it is important to\r\nchoose bright red berries, as white- or green-tipped strawberries are lacking\r\nin flavor. Don&acute;t overlook the little onesÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âsmall strawberries are often sweeter\r\nthan their big brothers.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\">Storage Tips:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\"> Refrigerate strawberries immediately.\r\nWash the berries gently in cool water just before you plan to eat them, leaving\r\nthe caps on until after they are washed.</span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:EN\" lang=\"EN\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\r\n\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:en\"=\"\" lang=\"EN\"><a href=\"http://ls.webmd.com/RealMedia/ads/click_lx.ads/webmd/healthcooking/L19/1899071443/x62/WebMD/P_Food_and_Fitness_Planner@TopPicks_Meals_Nutrients/Free_Tool_Track_What_You_Eat_TopPicks.html/744a554d366c49666b616f4141526d49\"><span style=\"display:none;mso-hide:all;background:white\">Free &amp; Easy Tool to\r\nTrack What You Eat </span></a><span style=\"display:none;mso-hide:all;\r\nbackground:white\">Brain Foods f</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 06:19:52','smallCONT-00144Draft 06, 300x310_spring_fruit_guide[1].jpg','midCONT-00144Draft 06, 300x310_spring_fruit_guide[1].jpg','bigCONT-00144Draft 06, 300x310_spring_fruit_guide[1].jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:08:12','USR-000001',3),('CONT-00145',NULL,'Spring Vegetable Guide',' How to choose the best vegetables for the spring season','<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Spring-fresh and\r\nnutrient-packed artichokes, asparagus, peas and salad greens are in season now.\r\nThis handy guide offers information on picking the best spring vegetables and\r\nthe health benefits of each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;\">Artichokes</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Italians\r\nhave a deep attachment to the artichoke, which is native to the Mediterranean\r\nand first appeared in modern records in Naples around 1400. When spring rolls\r\naround in Rome, artichokes are served every way possible, from deep-fried to\r\nthinly sliced raw and topped with shaved pecorino and fruity olive oil. Then\r\nwhen the season is over, frozen and canned artichokes are definitely\r\nconvenient, making artichokes a great addition to weeknight meals and quick\r\ndips.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\"> Plenty of fiber and a good amount of vitamin C, potassium and folate make\r\nartichokes an obvious healthy choice.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Shopping\r\nTip:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">\r\nLook for green, plump, compact heads. Brown spots on the scales may be\r\nunattractive but indicate that the artichokes have been frost-kissed and have\r\nimproved flavor.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Storage\r\nTip:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">\r\nRefrigerate in a plastic bag for up to 1 week.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Asparagus<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">King\r\nLouis XIV of France was so fond of asparagus he ordered greenhouses to grow the\r\ndelicacy year-round. Today, you don&acute;t need to be royalty to enjoy it anytime,\r\nbut it is the freshest and tastiest in spring.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#737373;\r\ndisplay:none;mso-hide:all;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Continue reading below...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\"> One stalk of asparagus contains just 4 calories and delivers healthy doses\r\nof folate, potassium and fiber.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Shopping\r\nTips:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">\r\nConsumers who choose spindly asparagus are actually missing the juicy\r\ntenderness of fatter, more robust spears. \"Elegantly thin\" asparagus\r\nis less sweet, more grassy and herbaceous. Shun any spear that appears\r\nshriveled or whose bud is spreading open.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Storage\r\nTip:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\"> If\r\nyou&acute;re not going to eat your asparagus within a day or two, stand it upright in\r\na glass of water to keep it hydrated.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Peas<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Only\r\nabout 5 percent of the peas grown in the world are actually eaten freshÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âmost\r\nare frozen or canned. Do your part to boost the statistics by indulging in\r\nfresh spring peasÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Âsnap, snow or English shelling. Choose snow peas or snap peas\r\nif you&acute;re looking for the tasty edible pods to throw in a salad or to simply\r\nsautÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â© and choose shelling varieties for the fun-to-open pods full of little\r\ngreen gems.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">What\r\nYou Get:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN\"> Bursting with nutrients, peas are a very good source of vitamin K,\r\nmanganese, vitamin C, iron, fiber, vitamin B1 and folate, as well as a good\r\nsource of a host of other vitamins and minerals.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Shopping\r\nTip:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">\r\nLook for peas with light, bright coloring without any brown, bruised, withering\r\nends.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Storage\r\nTip:</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">\r\nRefrigerate peas for 2 to 4 days.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Heading38\" style=\"line-height:12.0pt\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Salad Greens<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"node1\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Salads\r\nusing fresh, seasonal greens are an ideal way to get dinner on the table fast\r\nwithout spending much time in front of the stove. Sandwiches are good places\r\nfor greens too: try watercress on a tuna salad sandwich or arugula on a grilled\r\nvegetable sandwich.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-07 06:21:45','smallCONT-00145Draft 05, 300x310_spring_vegetable_guide[1].jpg','midCONT-00145Draft 05, 300x310_spring_vegetable_guide[1].jpg','bigCONT-00145Draft 05, 300x310_spring_vegetable_guide[1].jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00146',NULL,'Does Permanent Straightening Spoil Natural Hair?','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">Good hair day means a lot! And we go to unexplainable extents to\r\nmake our strands fall just the way we want them to. The latest solution being -\r\nPermanent hair straightening. This procedure turns your rebel curly hair into\r\npoker straight strands that look perfect 24*7. But does permanent hair\r\nstraightening damage your natural hair? Dr Apoorva Shah from Richfeel\r\nTrichology answers our queryÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦</font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:15.05pt;background:white\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trichorrhexis_nodosa\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Trichorrhexis\r\nNodosa</strong></a> is a defect in the hair shaft characterised by\r\nthickening or weak points (nodes) that cause the hair to break off easily. This\r\ngroup of conditions contributes to the appearance of hair loss, lack of growth\r\nand damaged looking hair. It is commonly seen in the patients who are into\r\nchemical treatments like colouring, perming, straightening. Colouring hair\r\ncauses chemical damage. It makes the hair strand dry and brittle. When you\r\ncolour your hair, the cuticle opens up and the colour enters the cortex making\r\nit brittle. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nWhen you are trying to change the shape of your hair, tremendous heat is\r\napplied on the hair so that the <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/protein\" target=\"_blank\">protein</a> cystine (which the hair is composed of) is\r\nconverted into cysteine. It is then manipulated to get the desired look. During\r\nthat process, 20% of the <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/protein\" target=\"_blank\">protein</a> gets converted into cystic acid which is the permanent\r\nloss. Breakages are very common because of heat.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nSo the next time you are thinking of playing with your hair chemically, please\r\ncheck on the hair damage it will lead to: <o:p></o:p></font></p>\r\n\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.05pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">Dry hair <o:p></o:p></font></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.05pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">Burnt hair <o:p></o:p></font></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.05pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">Hair needs continuous quoting of\r\n     heat protective product. <o:p></o:p></font></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.05pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">The damage to the hair is\r\n     irreversible <o:p></o:p></font></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.05pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">Chances of the cuticle getting\r\n     damaged are high if permanent straightening is done was a ill trained\r\n     beautician <o:p></o:p></font></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.05pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">Hair becomes brittle from gels,\r\n     sprays and chemicals used for hair straightening <o:p></o:p></font></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.05pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">Permanent hair straightening can\r\n     lead to split ends in the hair <o:p></o:p></font></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.05pt; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Verdana\" color=\"#666666\">Hair loses its natural texture</font></li></ul>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-11 09:38:10','smallCONT-00146Life Style - 07, You Ask We Answer  Does Permanent Straightening Spoil Natural Hair.j','midCONT-00146Life Style - 07, You Ask We Answer  Does Permanent Straightening Spoil Natural Hair.jpg','bigCONT-00146Life Style - 07, You Ask We Answer  Does Permanent Straightening Spoil Natural Hair.jpg','USR-000001','2013-12-11 09:39:44','USR-000001',6),('CONT-00147',NULL,'Expert Monsoon Make UP Mantras','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/monsoon\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 15.05pt;\">Monsoon</a><span style=\"color: rgb(3, 3, 3); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 15.05pt;\">\r\noften comes with surprise showers which can give a blow to your look in no\r\ntime. The essential trick of </span><a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/monsoon\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 15.05pt;\">monsoon</a><span style=\"color: rgb(3, 3, 3); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 15.05pt;\"> make up lies in using and storing your makeup\r\nproducts wisely. Though we won&acute;t advise you to quit using make up, but it&acute;ll be\r\njust wise for you to get hands-on professional help in order to carry your\r\nrainy look in fun and style. We asked </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(3, 3, 3); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 15.05pt;\">Bollywood makeup whiz, Vidya Tikari </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(3, 3, 3); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 15.05pt;\">to\r\ntell us a few make up mantras for </span><a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/monsoon\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 15.05pt;\">monsoon</a><span style=\"color: rgb(3, 3, 3); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 15.05pt;\"> which will keep you cheerful and glowing all season\r\nlong.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"line-height:15.05pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#030303\">\r\n<b><br>\r\n<strong>Stay away from heavy, creamy makeup.</strong></b> If\r\nthere&acute;s one <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/monsoon\" target=\"_blank\">monsoon</a>\r\nmakeup mantra you must follow, it should be to stay away from heavy, creamy\r\nmakeup. You need to pick products that will stay on in humid weather. So, go\r\nfor a good quality oil-free matte primer, and a light oil-free base. And choose\r\nonly water-proof kohl &amp; mascara, and water-resistant lipsticks.<br>\r\n<b><br>\r\n<strong>Keep the base as light and natural as possible.</strong></b>\r\nDuring the day, use a concealer sparingly to take care of under eye circles, <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/skin\" target=\"_blank\">skin</a> blemishes or\r\nany discolouration. If you need more coverage, then go for mineralise powder\r\nfoundation by MAC or Revlon.<br>\r\n<b><br>\r\n<strong>Skip the toning-moisturising bit once in a while.</strong></b>\r\nBut, no matter how badly you want to hit the bed, removing all your makeup -\r\nespecially during the monsoons - is an absolute must. Why? Because sleeping\r\nwith your makeup on is not only the best way to suffocate your skin, you could\r\nalso get rashes, infections and allergies with all the microbes that abound\r\nduring the monsoons.&nbsp;<br>\r\n<b><br>\r\n<strong>Never sleep in your party makeup. </strong></b>Sleeping\r\nin your party makeup can age your <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/skin\" target=\"_blank\">skin</a> almost 10 times more than normal. Overnight, your <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/skin\" target=\"_blank\">skin</a> will absorb\r\nall the chemicals from the make up and clog up pores which can cause breakouts\r\n&amp; make you prone to other <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/monsoon\" target=\"_blank\">monsoon</a> <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/skin\" target=\"_blank\">skin</a> maladies.&nbsp;<br>\r\n<b><br>\r\n<strong>Remove your makeup properly.</strong></b> To properly\r\nremove makeup, all you need is a good cleanser for your face and a gentle eye\r\nmakeup remover. Cetaphil is my favourite cleanser. Other good ones are from Marie\r\nKay, Lancome, Oriflame and Mac. For eye makeup removers, go for Clinique,\r\nOriflame, Bodyshop, or Marie Kay. Remember to use a slightly damp cotton wipe\r\nso that it doesn&acute;t drag on your <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/skin\" target=\"_blank\">skin</a>. You can follow up with Cetaphil cream. &nbsp;<br>\r\n<b><br>\r\n<strong>Share makeup tips, but not the makeup products. </strong></b>Make\r\nsure you wash all your makeup brushes thoroughly and regularly, and chuck out\r\nall the old, expired makeup. Stay away from in-store testers as they can be a\r\nhub of unknown bacterias and viruses. Also, wash your hands before and after\r\nyou apply makeup.&nbsp;<br>\r\n<b><br>\r\n<strong>Dazzling <a href=\"http://healthmeup.com/topic/monsoon\" target=\"_blank\">Monsoon</a> Make Up Ideas</strong><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<strong>ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ Cheeks. </strong></b>For the cheeks, apply a cheek\r\ntint like Benetint. This will give you a lovely hint of colour and will hold up\r\nlonger in humidity.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height:15.05pt;background:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#030303\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ Eyes. </span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#030303\">For the eyes, the colours of the season are blue and purple\r\ntones. Use blue coloured pencils around the lashline and apply lots of\r\nwaterproof mascara.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height:15.05pt;background:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#030303\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ Lips.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#030303\">\r\nAvoid lip glosses and go in for long-stay lipsticks in bright pinks or\r\ncorals.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height:15.05pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#030303\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ To &acute;fix&acute; the look, finish off by spraying on a &acute;fix it spray&acute;.\r\nThis is available with several brands like MAC &amp; Body Shop.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-11 09:40:32','smallCONT-00147Life Style - 08, makeuppp_600x450.jpg','midCONT-00147Life Style - 08, makeuppp_600x450.jpg','bigCONT-00147Life Style - 08, makeuppp_600x450.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',6),('CONT-00148',NULL,'Your Guide to Shiny Party Hair This Season','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;mso-line-height-alt:13.2pt;\r\nmso-outline-level:1;background:white;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">As the October heat seems to impound us with its intensity, the\r\nsomewhat welcome sun after the <a href=\"http://idiva.com/topic/monsoon\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;inherit&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:#FF3333;text-decoration:none;text-underline:none\">monsoon</span></a></span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">deluge brings with it some unwelcome changes;\r\nitchy and dry scalp and</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\"><a href=\"http://idiva.com/topic/hair\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;font-family:&quot;inherit&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;color:#FF3333;text-decoration:none;\r\ntext-underline:none\">hair</span></a></span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">that tends to get frizzy and limp due to excessive secretions by\r\nthe sebaceous glands. The pores on the scalp get clogged, thus leading to\r\ndandruff, patchy skin and in extreme cases,</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\"><a href=\"http://idiva.com/topic/hair\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;inherit&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;color:#FF3333;\r\ntext-decoration:none;text-underline:none\">hair</span></a></span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">fall. And while you may decide that it&acute;s not\r\nworth crying over split (!) ends, it&acute;s a sign of your</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\"><a href=\"http://idiva.com/topic/hair\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;inherit&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:#FF3333;text-decoration:none;text-underline:none\">hair</span></a></span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.65pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">in distress! So how can one reclaim lustrous\r\nhair, that too in the wake of the upcoming party season?</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n13.65pt;background:white;vertical-align:baseline\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#666666\">The\r\ngoodness of hair oil&nbsp;</span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#666666\">\r\n<span style=\"background:white\">While the world is going gaga over complicated</span></span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><a href=\"http://idiva.com/topic/hair\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt