tyle=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:\r\n115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Stock and save</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666;background:white\">: It&acute;s no secret that buying in bulk helps you\r\nsave money; and</span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><a href=\"http://idiva.com/topic/beauty-products\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#FF3333;text-decoration:none;text-underline:none\">beauty\r\nproducts</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666;background:white\">are no exception. Visit a wholesale market near\r\nyou and buy your beauty essentials for at least three months at a stretch. You\r\ncould also log on to websites that offer great deals on beauty paraphernalia.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-11 10:26:14','smallCONT-00150Life Style-03 How to Save.jpg','midCONT-00150Life Style-03 How to Save.jpg','bigCONT-00150Life Style-03 How to Save.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',3),('CONT-00151',NULL,'Dangerous Bacteria Can Lurk Inside Nose: Study','People who carry staph can transmit life-threatening infections in hospital setting','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:14.25pt;mso-outline-level:3;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Researchers tested 12\r\nhealthy people and found that formerly overlooked sites deep within the nose\r\nmay be reservoirs for </span><i style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Staphylococcus aureus</i><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">, which is a major cause of\r\ndisease. Nearly half of </span><i style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">S. aureus</i><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\"> strains are antibiotic-resistant.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">It&acute;s been known that <i>S.\r\naureus</i> can reside on the skin and at sites lower down in the nose. Although\r\nthere are ways to eliminate the bacteria, it typically returns in weeks or\r\nmonths.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">This new finding that the\r\nbacteria can be present further inside the nose may explain why this happens,\r\nthe Stanford University School of Medicine researchers said.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">\"About one-third of\r\nall people are persistent <i>S. aureus</i> carriers, another third are\r\noccasional carriers and a remaining third don&acute;t seem to carry <i>S. aureus</i>\r\nat all,\" study senior author Dr. David Relman, a professor of medicine and\r\nmicrobiology and immunology, said in a university news release.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">\"Not everyone who\r\ncarries <i>S. aureus</i> gets sick. When they&acute;re out walking the streets and\r\notherwise healthy, attempts to rid them of their <i>S. aureus</i> are not\r\nnecessary, and even sometimes futile,\" said Relman, who also is chief of\r\nthe infectious disease section at Veterans Affairs Palo Alto Health Care\r\nSystem, in <st1:state w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">California</st1:place></st1:state>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">\"But once a carrier\r\nenters a hospital with an underlying illness or a weakened immune system or a\r\nhigh likelihood of undergoing skin-penetrating procedures, <i>S. aureus</i>\r\ncarriage is a major liability,\" he said.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">If <i>S. aureus</i> gets\r\ninto the bloodstream through a wound, incision or catheter placement, it can\r\ncause potentially life-threatening problems such as <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/a-to-z-guides/sepsis-septicemia-blood-infection\">sepsis</a>,\r\n<a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/lung/tc/pneumonia-topic-overview\">pneumonia</a>\r\nor infection of heart valves.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Relman and his colleagues\r\nalso found that a type of bacteria called <i>Corynebacterium\r\npseudodiphtheriticum</i> may compete with <i>S. aureus</i> at the sites deep within\r\nthe nose. It&acute;s possible that <i>C. pseudodiphtheriticum</i> -- or some\r\nmolecular product it produces -- may prove useful in countering <i>S. aureus</i>\r\ninfections, the researchers said.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-21 07:19:59','smallCONT-00151Health - 01, Dangerous Bacteria Can Lurk Inside Nose.jpg','midCONT-00151Health - 01, Dangerous Bacteria Can Lurk Inside Nose.jpg','bigCONT-00151Health - 01, Dangerous Bacteria Can Lurk Inside Nose.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00152',NULL,'Understanding the Common Cold -- the Basics','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#705E3E;mso-ansi-language:EN\">What\r\nIs a Common Cold?</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Sneezing,\r\nscratchy throat, runny nose -- everyone knows the first miserable signs of a </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cold-and-flu/default.htm\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">common cold</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">. But what\r\nis a common cold really? What causes you to catch colds frequently while your\r\nbest friend stays well? And more importantly, how can you prevent getting a\r\ncold this season? Here are some common cold basics to help you protect yourself\r\nand your family from getting sick.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The\r\ncommon cold is a group of </span><a href=\"http://symptoms.webmd.com/zz-classic-symptomchecker\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">symptoms</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"> in the\r\nupper respiratory tract caused by a large number of different viruses. Although\r\nmore than 200 viruses can cause the common cold, the perpetrator is usually the\r\nrhinovirus, which is to blame for causing 10% to 40% of colds. Also, the\r\ncoronaviruses cause about 20% of colds and the respiratory syncytial virus\r\n(RSV) causes 10% of colds.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Although\r\nthe common cold is usually mild, it is a leading cause of doctor visits and\r\nmissed days from school and work. According to the CDC, 22 million school days\r\nare lost annually in the </span><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">U.S.</st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">\r\nbecause of the common cold. Some estimates state that Americans suffer 1\r\nbillion colds annually.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#705E3E;mso-ansi-language:EN\">How\r\na Common Cold Starts</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">With a\r\ncommon cold, you can catch it from another person who is infected with the\r\nvirus. This usually happens by touching a surface contaminated with cold germs\r\n-- a computer keyboard, doorknob, or eating utensil, for example -- and then\r\ntouching your nose or mouth. You can also catch a cold by encountering\r\nsecretions someone with a cold has sneezed into the air.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">A cold\r\nbegins when a cold virus attaches to the lining of your nose or throat. Your\r\nimmune system sends white blood cells out to attack this germ. Unless you&acute;ve\r\nencountered that exact strain of the virus before, the initial attack fails and\r\nyour body sends in reinforcements. Your nose and throat get inflamed and\r\nproduce a lot of mucus. With so much of your body&acute;s energy directed&nbsp;at\r\nfighting the cold virus, you&acute;re left feeling tired and miserable.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#705E3E;mso-ansi-language:EN\">&nbsp;</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">While\r\ngetting chilled or wet is not a cause of common colds, there are factors that\r\nmake you more susceptible to catching a cold virus. For example, you are more\r\nlikely to catch a common cold if you are excessively fatigued, have emotional\r\ndistress, or have </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/allergies/default.htm\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">allergies</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">\r\nwith nose and throat symptoms.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#705E3E;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Common\r\nCold Symptoms</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">With\r\nthe common cold, you may have </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cold-and-flu/cold-guide/cold-symptoms-types\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">cold\r\nsymptoms</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"> such as an itching or </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cold-and-flu/tc/sore-throat-topic-overview\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">sore\r\nthroat</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"> with sneezing, nasal congestion, watery eyes, and mucus drainage.\r\nMore severe symptoms, such as </span><a href=\"http://children.webmd.com/tc/fever-age-4-and-older-topic-overview\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">high\r\nfever</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"> or muscle aches, may indicate you have a flu rather than a cold.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-21 07:22:01','smallCONT-00152Health - 02,Understanding the Common Cold.jpg','midCONT-00152Health - 02,Understanding the Common Cold.jpg','bigCONT-00152Health - 02,Understanding the Common Cold.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',1),('CONT-00153',NULL,'Flu','You should know aobut Flu...','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Worried\r\nabout catching the </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cold-and-flu/default.htm\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">flu</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">?\r\nWant to learn some ways to prevent it? Then read on to learn more about\r\ninfluenza -- what it is, how it&acute;s spread, and who&acute;s at greatest risk for\r\ngetting it. Knowledge is power when it comes to </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cold-and-flu/flu-guide/flu-overview-facts\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">preventing\r\nflu</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#705E3E;mso-ansi-language:EN\">What\r\nIs the Flu?</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Influenza,\r\ncommonly known as the \"flu,\" is an extremely contagious respiratory\r\nillness caused by influenza A or B viruses. Flu appears most frequently in\r\nwinter and early spring. The flu virus attacks the body by spreading through\r\nthe upper and/or lower respiratory tract.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#705E3E;mso-ansi-language:EN\">What&acute;s\r\nthe difference between a cold and flu?</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The\r\ncommon cold and flu are both contagious viral infections of the respiratory\r\ntract. Although the symptoms can be similar, flu is much worse. A cold may drag\r\nyou down a bit, but the flu can make you shudder at the very thought of getting\r\nout of bed.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Congestion,\r\n</span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cold-and-flu/tc/sore-throat-topic-overview\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">sore\r\nthroat</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">, and sneezing are common with colds. Both cold and flu bring\r\ncoughing, headache, and chest discomfort. With the flu, though, you are likely\r\nto run a </span><a href=\"http://children.webmd.com/tc/fever-age-4-and-older-topic-overview\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">high\r\nfever</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"> for several days and have body aches, fatigue, and weakness. Symptoms\r\nof the flu also tend to come on abruptly. Usually, complications from colds are\r\nrelatively minor, but a severe case of flu can lead to a life-threatening\r\nillness such as </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/lung/tc/pneumonia-topic-overview\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">pneumonia</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 12pt;\">More than 100 types of cold\r\nviruses are known, and new strains of flu evolve every few years. Since both\r\ndiseases are viral, antibiotics cannot conquer cold or flu. Remember: </span><i style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; background-color: white; line-height: 12pt;\">Antibiotics\r\nonly treat bacterial infections.</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Two antiviral <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/drugs/index-drugs.aspx\">medications</a> are\r\navailable to treat flu. But there are no medications that specifically defeat\r\nthe common cold. Antibiotics may be helpful only if there is a secondary\r\nbacterial infection.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#705E3E;mso-ansi-language:EN\">How\r\nare stomach flu and influenza different?</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Stomach\r\nflu\" is a popular term, but not a true medical diagnosis. It&acute;s not\r\nuncommon to mistake gastroenteritis, which is what stomach flu is, for the\r\nviral infection we commonly call the \"flu.\" Gastroenteritis refers to\r\ninflammation of the gastrointestinal tract (stomach and intestines). Viruses\r\nare the most common cause of stomach flu. With gastroenteritis, you may have\r\nsymptoms such as abdominal cramps, nausea, vomiting, and </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/digestive-disorders/digestive-diseases-diarrhea\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">diarrhea</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#705E3E;mso-ansi-language:EN\">How\r\nis flu spread?</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">The flu virus is spread\r\nfrom person to person through respiratory secretions and typically sweeps\r\nthrough large groups of people who spend time in close contact, such as in </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/parenting/baby/tc/choosing-child-care-topic-overview\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">daycare</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 12pt;\">\r\nfacilities, classrooms, college dormitories, military barracks, offices, and\r\nnursing homes.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Flu is spread when you\r\ninhale droplets in the air that contain the flu virus, make direct contact with\r\nrespiratory secretions through sharing drinks or utensils, or handle items\r\ncontaminated by an infected person. In the latter case, the flu virus on your\r\nskin can infect you when you touch or rub your eyes, nose, or mouth. That&acute;s why\r\nfrequent and thorough handwashing is a key way to limit the spread of\r\ninfluenza. Flu symptoms start to develop from one to four days after infection\r\nwith the virus.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-21 07:24:56','smallCONT-00153Health - 03, Flu -Topic Overview.jpg','midCONT-00153Health - 03, Flu -Topic Overview.jpg','bigCONT-00153Health - 03, Flu -Topic Overview.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',1),('CONT-00154',NULL,'Coughs - Topic Overview','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Coughing\r\nis the body&acute;s way of removing foreign material or mucus from the </span><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/lung/respiratory-system-18881\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">lungs and upper\r\nairway passages</a><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">or of reacting to an irritated\r\nairway. Coughs have distinctive traits you can learn to recognize. A cough is\r\nonly a symptom, not a disease, and often the importance of your cough can be\r\ndetermined only when other symptoms are evaluated.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"line-height: 12pt;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:red;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Productive\r\ncoughs</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">A productive cough produces\r\nphlegm or mucus (sputum). The mucus may have drained down the back of the\r\nthroat from the nose or sinuses or may have come up from the lungs. A\r\nproductive cough generally should not be suppressed-it clears mucus from the\r\nlungs. There are many causes of a productive cough, such as:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Viral illnesses</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">. It is normal to have a\r\nproductive cough when you have a common cold. Coughing is often triggered by\r\nmucus that drains down the back of the throat. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Infections</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">. An infection of the lungs\r\nor upper airway passages can cause a cough. A productive cough may be a symptom\r\nof <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/pneumonia\">pneumonia</a>, <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/bronchitis\">bronchitis</a>, <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/sinusitis\">sinusitis</a>, or <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/tuberculosis\">tuberculosis</a>. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Chronic lung disease</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">. A productive cough could\r\nbe a sign that a disease such as <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/chronic-obstructive-pulmonary-disease-copd\">chronic\r\nobstructive pulmonary disease</a> (COPD) is getting worse or that you have an\r\ninfection. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Stomach acid backing up into the <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/digestive-disorders/esophagus-18947\"><span style=\"color:red\">esophagus</span></a></span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"> <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/digestive-disorders/esophagus-18947\"><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape\r\n id=\"_x0000_i1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"camera\" style=&acute;width:9pt;height:8.25pt&acute;\r\n o:button=\"t\">\r\n <v:imagedata src=\"file:///C:UsersUserAppDataLocalTempmsohtmlclip1\01clip_image001.gif\"\r\n  o:href=\"http://img.webmd.com/dtmcms/live/webmd/consumer_assets/site_images/media/interface/camera.gif\"/>\r\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img border=\"0\" width=\"12\" height=\"11\" src=\"file:///C:UsersUserAppDataLocalTempmsohtmlclip1\01clip_image001.gif\" alt=\"camera\" v:shapes=\"_x0000_i1026\"><!--[endif]--></a>. This type of coughing may be\r\na symptom of <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/reflux-disease\">gastroesophageal\r\nreflux disease</a> (GERD) and may awaken you from sleep. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Nasal discharge</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"> (<a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/postnasal-drip\">postnasal drip</a>)\r\ndraining down the back of the throat. This can cause a productive cough or the\r\nfeeling that you constantly need to clear your throat. Experts disagree about\r\nwhether a postnasal drip or the viral illness that caused it is responsible for\r\nthe cough. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Smoking or other tobacco use</span></b><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">. Productive coughs in a\r\nperson who smokes or uses other forms of tobacco is often a sign of lung damage\r\nor irritation of the throat or esophagus.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:7.5pt;line-height:12.0pt;mso-outline-level:\r\n5;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:red;mso-ansi-language:EN\">Nonproductive\r\ncoughs<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:2.25pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;background:white\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">A nonproductive cough is\r\ndry and does not produce sputum. A dry, hacking cough may develop toward the\r\nend of a cold or after exposure to an irritant, such as dust or smoke. There\r\nare many causes of a nonproductive cough, such as:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Viral illnesses. After a common cold, a dry\r\ncough may last several weeks longer than other symptoms and often gets worse at\r\nnight. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Bronchospasm. A nonproductive cough,\r\nparticularly at night, may mean spasms in the bronchial tubes (bronchospasm)\r\ncaused by irritation. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Allergies. Frequent sneezing is also a common\r\nsymptom of <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/allergic-rhinitis-hay-fever\">allergic\r\nrhinitis</a>. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Medicines called ACE inhibitors that are used\r\nto control <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/high-blood-pressure-hypertension\">high\r\nblood pressure</a>. Examples of ACE inhibitors include captopril (Capoten),\r\nenalapril maleate (Vasotec), and lisinopril (Prinivil, Zestril, or Zestoretic).\r\n<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Exposure to dust, fumes, and chemicals in the\r\nwork environment. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/asthma\">Asthma</a>.\r\nA chronic dry cough may be a sign of mild asthma. Other symptoms may include\r\nwheezing, shortness of breath, or a feeling of tightness in the chest. For more\r\ninformation, see the topic <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/asthma/tc/asthma-in-teens-and-adults-overview\">Asthma\r\nin Teens and Adults</a>. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\">ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â·<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &acute;Times New Roman&acute;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Blockage of the airway by an inhaled object,\r\nsuch as food or a pill. For more information, see the topic <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/first-aid/tc/swallowed-objects-topic-overview\">Swallowed\r\nObjects</a>.</span></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-21 07:26:46','smallCONT-00154Health - 04, Teen_girl_coughing.jpg','midCONT-00154Health - 04, Teen_girl_coughing.jpg','bigCONT-00154Health - 04, Teen_girl_coughing.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00155',NULL,'Fashion show exhibits eco-friendly clothing','The show was an outcome of an ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Ethno Fashion WorkshopÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â in which Michael Sontag from Germany, Sakina MÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â´Sa from France and Bibi Russell from Bangladesh guided ten young','<span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">A dazzling fashion show was held on June 7 at the Alliance FranÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â§aise de Dhaka (AFD), where ramp models walked in eco-friendly pieces of clothing made by young Bangladeshi designers.&nbsp; The show was an outcome of an ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Ethno Fashion WorkshopÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â in which Michael Sontag from Germany, Sakina MÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â´Sa from France and Bibi Russell from Bangladesh guided ten young Bangladeshi designers. Twenty-three models walked in La Galerie and in the AFD courtyard dressed in colourful and exquisitely designed outfits that marked the passage of time from day wear to night dress. The models, virtually all non-professionals, had been trained at Alliances FranÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â§aise during a series of catwalk workshops led by Bibi Russell.&nbsp; The show ended with a parade of the ten designers whose names were presented to the audience. The participating designers were: Nazia Afroz, Iffat Ara, Rubaiya Haque Raka, Homaira Hasin Sadia, Tasmit Afiyat (Arny), Kehkasha Sabah, Sifat Zaman, Yaana Nuzhat, Jarin Tasnim Ona and Md Hanif Kaiser. They displayed products of a very elaborate fusion of inspirations, bringing together three strands of fashion designing tradition into single works of art. The aim of the workshop was to give fresh impetus to the design scene in Bangladesh and to show the creativity and the opportunities of BangladeshÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â´s fashion scene, sending a much needed positive message in the light of recent events. Two of the young designers have already been invited to the Berlin Fashion Week in July. The project is now moving to Chittagong where Alliance FranÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â§aise will organize two shows on Monday June 10 at 6:30pm and 9pm. The dresses will be on display at Alliance FranÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â§aise de Dhaka in the later part of the year.&nbsp;</span><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">Courtesy: dhakatribune.com</span></div>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-21 07:33:10','smallCONT-00155Dhakatribune.jpg','midCONT-00155Dhakatribune.jpg','bigCONT-00155Dhakatribune.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',3),('CONT-00156',NULL,'Eye care tips for summer ','Summer heat not only do these affect your skin and hair but your eyes as well','<div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;\"><b>Eye care tips for summer</b></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">The scorching heat during the daytime can harm your eyes. Here are a few tips to tell you how to keep those ocular problems at bay this time of the year. Summer is typical with dust, heat and excessive sunlight. Not only do these affect your skin and hair but your eyes as well. ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Just as we use sunscreen and other protections from the harmful UV rays of the sun, similarly we need to protect our eyes too. Overexposure to ultraviolet rays of the sun can lead to cataract, retinal damage and other eye problems as well,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â Surgeon Dr Keiki Mehta suggested in a UNB report quoting The Times of India.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\"><b><br></b></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\"><b>Choose a pair of good sunglasses</b></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">UV treatment in eyeglass lenses blocks the rays from damaging your eyes. Adds Mehta, ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“For summer, the ideal sunglasses are those with a wrap around frame. It keeps sun, dust and grime out.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â Apart from this, consider opting for polarised lenses as they reduce the glare from reflective surfaces and are great if you&acute;re keen about water-based activities and driving.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;\"><b>Eye protection while swimming</b></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">The cool water is quite inviting on a hot day, but do not forget to take care of your eyes from the chlorine in the pool. In this weather, the incidence of skin infection in swimming pool rises, thus it can lead to eye irritation. While swimming, consider using goggles and afterwards, wash and rinse your eyes properly with fresh water to reduce the redness that is caused due to chlorine water. Eye drop can help It is not only your skin that dries out during summer, but also your eyes. Eye experts claim using lubricating drops will prevent your eyes from getting itchy. Use an eye pack Do not just treat your skin and mane, but consider using a cooling eye pack once in a while. You can place two pieces of cucumber on your eyes before going off to bed or rather, just spray some rose water to keep your eyes fresh and cool.</span></div>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-21 07:42:40','smallCONT-00156Dhakatribune.jpg','midCONT-00156Dhakatribune.jpg','bigCONT-00156Dhakatribune.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',3),('CONT-00157',NULL,'Take care of your hair','Style your hair with gel and also take proper care to prevent hair damage','<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">Among the hair styling products gel is one of the most used. Looking trendy and managing your hair is the main purpose of using hair gel. Though it&acute;s a unisex product but men use it more than women.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">Hair gel helps you to cement your hair for the whole day. You can style your hair waved, spiked, straight with gel.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">But some gels or other hair products that contain alcohol will dry out and damage your hair.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">In this case, you need to take care of your hair.</p><ul style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 10px 25px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\"><li>&nbsp; While using gel put it carefully so that it doesn&acute;t touch your scalp. When gel reaches the scalp, the root of hair becomes weak and causes hair fall.</li><li>Use gel in when your hair is dry. Wet hair consumes the chemicals present in gel which results hair breaking in the middle.</li><li>Try to avoid hard gel. Hard gels should not be used until your hair is too heavy to manage with soft gels.</li><li>Use hard gel occasionally, not every day.</li><li>Your hairs gather a lot of dust while working outside. Before going to bed wash your hair.</li><li>As you are using hair gel, you should do shampoo regularly. Use conditioner after shampoo.</li><li>It&acute;s the best if you oil your hair before going to bed and then wash it with shampoo in the morning. This will make your hair healthy.</li><li>Don&acute;t use comb in wet hair, it causes hair damage too.</li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">On average we lose around 100 hairs per day. It&acute;s natural. But if your hair fall turns huge, you need to take it seriously.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;\">Take proper care of your hair. Style your hair according to your personality. Hair is very precious and realise it before being a bald.</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-21 07:49:32','smallCONT-00157Dhakatribune.jpg','midCONT-00157Dhakatribune.jpg','bigCONT-00157Dhakatribune.jpg','USR-00