s=\"aol-knot-fullscreen-title\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Shiseido Eyelash Curler</div><div class=\"aol-knot-fullscreen-caption\"><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1em;\">You&acute;ve got your mascara, but don&acute;t forget to pack the must-have eyelash curler! Create beautifully curled lashes in just one squeeze for a glamorous look you can do in seconds.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1em;\"><br></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-23 08:57:52','smallCONT-00158cosmetic-bag-selects-122013.jpg','midCONT-00158cosmetic-bag-selects-122013.jpg','bigCONT-00158cosmetic-bag-selects-122013.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',9),('CONT-00159',NULL,'Find the best oil for your hair type','','<div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Beauty trends come and go. Over time women and men have slathered, concocted, made potions, bought potions and traveled to the ends of the earth in search of better skin, nails and hair.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">So it is no wonder that I sit here to write this post about a trend that isn&acute;t so much a new thing .. but a newly remembered thing..</span><div style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center;\"><strong>Hair oil..</strong></div></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">If there is one thing that I have learned over the years it&acute;s that.. HAIR NEEDS OIL!</span><br style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Now there is that small percentage of people who can wash their hair with a bar of soap, never use an ounce of product and manage to have the most beautiful thick shiny head of hair. I remember when I was a kid hearing my mother tell me that she read an article with uber famous iconic model Jerry Hall who is known for her long beautiful blond locks. In this article she confessed to the magazine that she only washes her hair once a month with scalp cleanses in between. I know. Like whoa.. I get to day 4 and I am ready to pull my hear out. Pun intended.</span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">But what Jerry Hall and a good percentage of women knew and still know is that washing your hair strips it of the natural oils it needs to look shiny and healthy.</span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Now I am not going to lie. I will never join the one month wash club. So this is where the aforementioned beauty trend comes into play. Hair oil is essential.. essential to gain and maintain a luscious head of hair.</span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 14.666666984558105px; line-height: 34.66666793823242px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></div><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ProximaNova-Regular; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">But today it&acute;s just super hard to know what to choose. While raw Coconut oil is great for pre-wash treatments and Jojoba oil is great for naturally curly hair, Argan oil is perfect for a blowout and Ojon oil is great for all the above. So whats a girl to do? I put together a list of hair oils for you to sift through. Depending on your hair what is right for you</span>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-23 09:14:04','smallCONT-00159stuff-she-likes-9.jpg','midCONT-00159stuff-she-likes-9.jpg','bigCONT-00159stuff-she-likes-9.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',3),('CONT-00160',NULL,'Top 8 Ways To Upgrade Your Bathroom Or Closet (No Handyman Required!)','','<p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Believe it or not, you can help reenergize and reorganize yourself with a freshly decorated bathroom and closet. Since we start off every new day in either one of these spaces, it makes it an important part of our every daily routine and reflects the way we tackle our daily schedule. Here are some easy ideas you can do right at home to turn a bland bathroom or closet into a glamorous gem (no handy man required!).</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">Top 8 Ways To Upgrade A Bathroom Or Closet:</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">Upgrade Your Faucet</strong><br>You would be amazed at what a simple upgrade can do for a bathroom. Long gone are the days of chrome faucets, they look cold and don&acute;t bring much warmth to your bathroom. Install a shiny gold faucet to instantly bring in a dash of luxury to your bathroom&acute;s hardware. A shiny gold soap dish to match and you&acute;re set!</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">Purchase A New Rug</strong><br>Roll out a new rug in your closet to keep your toes warm and bring in a hint of color to this dark space. An eclectic circular area rug can make your closet feel like a boutique and make you leave your home feeling like a diva.</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">Install A New Towel Bar</strong><br>If you still have that towel bar the builders put in when you first purchased your home, it&acute;s time for a new one. Don&acute;t buy a clear plastic towel bar since they can fill up with visible mold and end up looking like a mess. Instead opt for brushed bronze, which brings in warmth and really matches with all kinds of color schemes and dÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â©cor.</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">Try No-Grout Tiles</strong><br>Re-tiling a bathroom used to be a hassle and required a skilled handyman to do it. With more DIY-ers out there, DBS Bathrooms has made our lives a little easier with peel and stick wall panels. They are SO easy to fit, cut, customize, and require no mess at all opposed to regular tiles with grout.</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">Revamp Your Shelves</strong><br>Wallpaper the back of your closet shelves with a bright, metallic paper to reflect and shine behind your shoes and clothing. I love the look of metallic leopard print paper, which brings in a wild and boutique feeling to my closet.</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">Focus On Lighting</strong><br>Bring in as much light as possible into your bathroom or closet by hanging up a mini chandelier to reflect light and make your space feel like a small jewel box.</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">Install New Hardware</strong><br>Install new hardware on drawers, dressers, and shelves to immediately refreshen up tired looking storage spaces. You would be surprised at what a difference this can make! Match them to your new faucet&acute;s hardware for a uniform look.</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-23 09:57:27','smallCONT-00160Transform-Bathroom-Closet-122013_0.jpg','midCONT-00160Transform-Bathroom-Closet-122013_0.jpg','bigCONT-00160Transform-Bathroom-Closet-122013_0.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',6),('CONT-00161',NULL,'5 Tricks To Make Your Home Look Bigger','','<p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Make your home look bigger and brighter with the right kind of flooring to open it up and make it seem like it runs for miles! Okay we can&acute;t make it look this big but we can try! Check out these top 5 tricks from the pros:</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">1. Install Flooring Diagonally</strong><br>Laying flooring diagonally across your room will make it instantly look bigger. If you are using hardwood, stone, or laminate, the rule applies for all.</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">2. Use Planks Not Strips</strong><br>Visually expand your space by starting with your hardwood floors. Strips are boards that are skinnier than 3 inches and planks are wider than 3 inches. Pick the longest wall in your room and run them parallel to this way to make your room run for miles!</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">3. Keep It Consistent</strong><br>Instead of installing a different type of flooring for each space in your home, use the same type of flooring throughout. This way you will create a ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“seamlessÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â look that ties one room directly into another giving the illusion of having more space.</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">4. Use Oversized Tiles</strong><br>The standard 12ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â porcelain tiles scream ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ outdated builders tiles! Choose a great tile bigger than 12ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â to give the look of an expansive space that ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“breathesÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â.</p><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: proxima-nova; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"font-style: inherit;\">5. Opt For Dark Woods</strong><br>Dark wood floors will make your space look bigger if paired with th