t: 24px;\">9. Love Scents</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-size: 14px;\">When it&acute;s still cold outside but your heart is full of love on February 14, set the Valentine&acute;s Day mood with simmering cinnamon sticks and vanilla, or burn a cinnamon spice candle to heat things up. You also can&acute;t go wrong with fresh rose petals for a welcome bouquet with a burst of fragrance.</p></div><div class=\"slideshow-item slideoff\" style=\"width: 602px; padding: 10px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; overflow: hidden; opacity: 1; float: left; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: -642px; background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249); border-right-width: 1px; border-right-style: solid; border-right-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); min-height: 468px; -webkit-transition: left 350ms ease-in; transition: left 350ms ease-in; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px; z-index: 9;\"><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">8. Spring Fling</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-size: 14px;\">Fresh flowers might not be blooming in your garden, but you can pick up hothouse spring blooms in your grocery store or home store. Roses, lilies, and gardenias are some of the most fragrant choices.</p></div><div class=\"slideshow-item slideoff\" style=\"width: 602px; padding: 10px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; overflow: hidden; opacity: 1; float: left; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: -642px; background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249); border-right-width: 1px; border-right-style: solid; border-right-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); min-height: 468px; -webkit-transition: left 350ms ease-in; transition: left 350ms ease-in; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px; z-index: 8;\"><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">7. Spring Scents</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-size: 14px;\">Make your home smell of spring by simmering a pot on the stove, filled about 2/3 of the way with water. Add thinly sliced lemons, a few sprigs of rosemary and a splash or two of vanilla or another springy essential oil. Your still-chilly home will smell fresh and light!</p></div><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">6. Tropical Delights</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">While you might associate potpourri with the colder months, this simmering home scent is ideal for the summer when you want clean, breezy scents. In a saucepan, add two sliced lemons, two sliced limes, a sliced orange and a can of pineapple juice. Add coconut or vanilla extract and simmer until the juice is cooked down.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">5. Beach Days</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Whether you&acute;re overlooking the ocean or landlocked at home, having your house smell like the ocean can take you away from it all. Add sliced lemons, vanilla extract and sprigs of fresh rosemary to a simmering pan. You want to keep the water low on this scent, to let the vanilla and rosemary waft through the air ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ and you&acute;ll almost feel the sea breeze on your skin.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">4. October Spice</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Suddenly leaves are blowing up the sidewalk and you&acute;re craving a fall scent for your home ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ how about using that jack o&acute; lantern? Scrape out your pumpkin like you normally would (carving and all) but make sure there are vents or holes all around to let the scent out. Then sprinkle the inside with your favorite yummy fall spice ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ cloves, pumpkin pie, cinnamon ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ and when you set a tea light in the pumpkin, it will smell fantastic.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">3. Give Thanks</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Thanksgiving is full of food, family and fun, but all that cooking and company can leave your home smelling a little stale. Simmer a pot of water (about 2/3 full) with lemon slices, star anise, cinnamon and a dash of pumpkin pie spice. You&acute;ll have the smell of Thanksgiving and dessert wafting through your home, even once dinner is over and everyone&acute;s cozied up in front of the football game.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">2. Scents of Christmas</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The year is closing, Santa is coming and the house is full of cheer. Refresh the air with a Christmas-themed home scent by simmering a pot of water with orange slices, nutmeg and cinnamon. This simple scent will put the whole family in a holiday mood (and guarantee your spot on the ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“NiceÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â list).</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">1. It&acute;s Cold Out There</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Another variation on a December home scent will make you feel warm and cozy while the snow is falling. In a simmering pot of water, or in your slow cooker, mix a handful of bay leaves, some pine twigs (cedar works as well) and nutmeg. If you have a whole nutmeg, use a microplane to grate off the outside and release the scent and then toss the whole nutmeg in to simmer (or add about a teaspoon of pre-grated nutmeg if that&acute;s what you have on hand).</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><br></p></div>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-31 10:06:21','smallCONT-00164seasonalhome.jpg','midCONT-00164seasonalhome.jpg','bigCONT-00164seasonalhome.jpg','USR-000001','2013-12-31 10:29:05','USR-000001',7),('CONT-00165',NULL,'4 GREEN WAYS TO KEEP YOUR HOUSE FRESH','','<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Avoiding aerosols is as important as avoiding a typical room air-freshening sprayer. YÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â­ou can achieve the same effect -- a clean, fresh-smelling house -- with your own nontoxic concoctions. As an added bonus, you can mix and match scents to suit your own fragrance tastes!</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Keep reading to learn about keeping your house fresh naturally. First up, DIY air freshener.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">4. DIY Freshener</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The human sense of smell is a very sensitive thing, so much so that a clean-smelling home can play a large part in your emotional and physical health. Make your own earth-friendly freshener spray by mixing equal parts lemon juice and water and storing it in a spray bottle you&acute;ve salvaged from some of your old cleaning products (make sure to rinse it out well first). Spray this around your home once or twice a week for odor control, or as needed when cooking or to get rid of smells that have seeped into the draperies, couch, and other fabrics.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">3. Simmering Scents</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">One way to spice up your home is by simmering a little cinnamon, cloves, fresh ginger, and the herbs of your choice in a bit of water on your stovetop. For a more summery smell, try adding a handful of mint leaves to 8 cups water. Bring the mixture to a boil first and then turn down to a simmer. You can also use essential oils in combination with these spices, or alone.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">2. Scent on the Spot</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">For rooms that need freshening in a jiff, soak cotton balls in vanilla extract or an essential oil. Place the cotton in a pretty dish or jar wherever you need to refresh the air. You can also just pour a little vanilla extract into a small bowl and place it where needed.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><br></p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">1. Houseplants</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">NASA (the National Aeronautics and Space Administration) has determined that some common houseplants can do a world of good at eliminating nasty toxins that may be in your home. After all, indoor air quality is a matter of some concern: Along with everyday carcinogens such as secondhand smoke (which contains sulfur dioxide), common household products may also be emitting chemicals into the air we breathe. One of these chemicals is formaldehyde, which can be found in clothes, plywood, and carpeting, leading to headaches and breathing problems.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">NASA studied three common indoor pollutants -- trichloroethylene, formaldehyde, and benzene -- and concluded that the average home could benefit from keeping about 15 plants around. Plants work to gently remove these toxins from your indoor air by producing oxygen, adding moisture to the air, and absorbing the bad stuff through their leaves. Consider them nature&acute;s filter!</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Here are some houseplants to consider adding to your indoor plant collection:</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The Boston fern (Nephrolepi exalta \"Bostoniensis\"), florist&acute;s mum (Chrysanthemum morifolium), gerbera daisy (Gerbera jamesonii), dwarf date palm (Phoenix roebelenii), areca palm (Chrysalidocarpus lutescens), moth orchid (Phalenopsis), bamboo palm (Chamaedorea), Chinese evergreen (Aglaonema), English ivy (Hedera helix), indoor dracaenas (Dracaena \"Janet Craig,\" D. marginata, D. massangeana, and D. warnekii), and the snake plant or mother-in-law&acute;s tongue (Sansevieria trifasciata laurentii).</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-31 10:09:25','smallCONT-001654-tips-to-keeping-your-house-fresh-1.jpg','midCONT-001654-tips-to-keeping-your-house-fresh-1.jpg','bigCONT-001654-tips-to-keeping-your-house-fresh-1.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',3),('CONT-00166',NULL,'5 THINGS IN YOUR BATHROOM YOU SHOULD CLEAN EVERYDAY','','<a href=\"http://tlc.howstuffworks.com/home/how-to-clean-bathroom.htm\" style=\"color: rgb(30, 108, 128); text-decoration: none; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249);\">Cleaning the bathroom</a><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249);\">&nbsp;is a job few want to tackle -- and rightfully so. There are some scary things in there. Soap scum, bacteria, toilet rings -- it&acute;s almost as if they saved the slimiest names for bathroom grime. So why would anyone want to clean the bathroom daily? Well, as it turns out, there are parts of the bathroom that are pretty easy to clean as you use them every day. And, if you get in the habit of giving these surfaces a quick cleaning each time you use them, you&acute;ll make the big deep-clean job a lot easier to handle, whether you choose to do it weekly or bi-weekly. Read on as we share the five things in your bathroom that deserve a daily cleaning.</span><div><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">5: Sink(s)</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Cleaning out the sink is easy enough. But if you don&acute;t give it a good wipe each day, soap scum, hard water and even your makeup can build up and leave your sink looking dingy. Depending on what type of material your sink is made of, staining can even occur over time. But not to worry, a daily cleaning will prevent stains and keep your sink looking squeaky clean. Wiping the sink out each day when you finish your morning routine will save your arms a good deal of scrubbing, too. To guard against a dingy sink and stubborn, built-up grime, simply keep a sponge under your sink or in the medicine cabinet. Give the sink a good wipe as the very last step of your morning routine, and voilÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â  -- the days of vigorously scrubbing your sink are over.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">4: Toilet Touch-up</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249);\">The dreaded toilet -- it&acute;s probably everyone&acute;s least favorite part of&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://tlc.howstuffworks.com/home/how-to-clean-bathroom.htm\" style=\"color: rgb(30, 108, 128); text-decoration: none; background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249);\">cleaning the bathroom</a><span style=\"background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249);\">. But, this dirty job can be made easier with a little daily maintenance. Don&acute;t have enough money for all that&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://tlc.howstuffworks.com/home/keep-the-toilet-bowl-clean.htm\" style=\"color: rgb(30, 108, 128); text-decoration: none; background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249);\">toilet bowl</a><span style=\"background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249);\">cleaner? Well, that&acute;s OK. You won&acute;t need it. Simply wipe down the seat and lid with an antibacterial wipe and swirl the toilet bowl brush around the toilet bowl. There will be enough toilet bowl cleaner left on the brush from your weekly cleanings to kill germs each day with a quick swish.</span></p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">3: Mirror, Faucets and Countertop</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Although they&acute;re not as obvious at collecting germs as other areas in your bathroom, your mirror, faucets and countertop could use a daily cleaning as well. The perfect time to perform this cleaning is at the end of your morning routine (you know, at the same time you&acute;re giving your sink its daily cleaning). A sponge with a gentle cleaner is the perfect tool for your faucets and countertop. Don&acute;t forget to reach the tight spaces between your faucet and the back wall and in the seams where the faucets attach to the countertops. These areas are dirt magnets, and yet are often missed in a quick cleaning. Glass cleaner and a paper towel should be used for the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://tlc.howstuffworks.com/home/5-tricks-to-cleaning-windows-and-mirrors.htm\" style=\"color: rgb(30, 108, 128); text-decoration: none;\">mirrors</a>. If you&acute;re having trouble with streaking, try using newspaper instead of a paper towel</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">2: Shower Curtain/Door</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Your shower curtains or doors aren&acute;t just magnets for soap scum; they can also be breeding grounds for mildew and bacteria -- yuck! To prevent this gritty, unwanted film from building up on your door or curtain, you&acute;ll need to give them a quick cleaning each day -- or each time you use the shower, anyway. If you&acute;re in a hurry, a quick rinse with hot water will help keep a shower curtain clean. Don&acute;t forget to pull the curtain shut when you&acute;re finished. A bunched up curtain holds water in its folds and promotes the growth of mildew. If you have a shower door, use a squeegee to clean it after each use to keep it shiny and new. Turning on the exhaust fan during and after your shower will also help prevent mildew from forming.</p><h2 class=\"slideshow-item-title\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 5px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ClarendonTextProRegular, serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 22px; line-height: 24px;\">1: Shower/Tub</h2><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249);\">Just like your shower curtain or door, the tub or floor of your shower is prone to mildew and soap scum build-up, too. The reason your shower requires daily attention is its climate. Constant moisture creates a breeding ground for unwanted grime. Get rid of any extra moisture in your shower or tub by using a squeegee or a towel to sop up extra water left after use. If your shower is made of tiles, the caulking in between each tile should be given special attention, as mildew thrives in this particular environment. Keeping the bathroom fan on during and after your shower will help wick up moisture as well. For even cleaner, shinier shower walls and tub, try a shower spray. Simply spritz the shower walls, floors, or tub on your way out, and your work here is done.</span></p></div>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-31 10:18:58','smallCONT-00166clean-bath-daily-250x150.jpg','midCONT-00166clean-bath-daily-250x150.jpg','bigCONT-00166clean-bath-daily-250x150.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',3),('CONT-00167',NULL,'Clean Your Kitchen in 5 Minutes or Less','Here are 10 steps for cleaning the kitchen in 5 minutes or less:','<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Have you ever looked at your disastrous kitchen and just couldn&acute;t bear the thought of tackling the mess?&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">I sure hope you are nodding your head yes! It will make me feel so much better if I&acute;m not the only one.</em></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There are days&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">(if I&acute;m honest I would say EVERY day)</em>&nbsp;that I don&acute;t feel like cleaning the kitchen. That&acute;s why I have to play a little mind game with myself. I have to trick myself into cleaning the kitchen.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">I set the timer for 5 minutes and&nbsp;<strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">compete with myself&nbsp;</strong>to see how fast I can clean the kitchen.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">First, set the timer.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Then get a game plan together and&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">work the plan</em>.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Ready, set, go!</p><ol style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Dirty Dishes</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Gather all dirty dishes from around the house (*ahem*) and bring them to the kitchen. Move fast!</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Trash</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Pick up all the trash off the counters (see how much you can carry at once) and throw it away.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Refrigerator</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Grab everything that goes in the refrigerator and put it where it belongs. Try to make it in one trip.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Cabinets</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Gather everything that belongs in the cabinets and put it in the correct location. Again, try to make one trip.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Utensils</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Pick up all dirty utensils (forks, spoons, knives, spatulas) from the counters and sink to put in the dishwasher&acute;s silverware basket.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Cups/Glasses/Mugs</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Gather all drinking glasses to put on the top shelf of the dishwasher. Try to put similar cups beside each other but don&acute;t get too hung up on it. Remember the timer is on!</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Plates</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ If you have more than one size plate, start with the smallest size and load them in the dishwasher. Then work your way up to the larger sizes.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Everything else</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Grab all of the big items (pots, pans, strainers, cutting boards) and either put them in the dishwasher or wash them by hand.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Start the dishwasher</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Only if it&acute;s full of course.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Wash and dry the counters</strong>&nbsp;ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Wipe down the stove, microwave, and any other appliance that&acute;s dirty with one hand and use another rag to dry with the other hand.</li></ol><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Stop the timer. Check to see if you cleaned your kitchen in under five minutes.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Celebrate if you did!</em></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Now you can leave your sparkling kitchen with your wash cloth and dish rags, put them in the laundry basket and enjoy the rest of your day. While you&acute;re on your way out, take anything else that doesn&acute;t belong in the kitchen and put the items where they belong.<strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Do you see the trick? It&acute;s not about following the steps exactly. It&acute;s about keeping like items together and doing like functions at the same time. Clean your kitchen by taking as few steps as possible.</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We don&acute;t want to get sidetracked by cleaning a few dishes, then going to the refrigerator, then throwing something away.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">It breaks the flow.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">When we keep similar functions together we take fewer steps, thus cutting cleaning time tremendously!</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There&acute;s another benefit of loading like items together in the dishwasher. When it&acute;s time to unload and put the dishes away, it saves a ton of time!<strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 27px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Arial, &acute;Helvetica Neue&acute;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 27px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">If you ARE the dishwasher, I feel for you. Please feel free to share your tips for cleaning your kitchen quickly without a dishwasher.</strong></p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2013-12-31 10:45:32','smallCONT-00167keep-kitchen-sponges-clean-1.jpg','midCONT-00167keep-kitchen-sponges-clean-1.jpg','bigCONT-00167keep-kitchen-sponges-clean-1.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:01:52','USR-000001',1),('CONT-00168',NULL,'Bengali Hilsa Fish Fry','Bengali Hilsa Fish Fry Recipe','Do you know what is favorite fish for Bengalis? If you ask anybody, I \r\nthink you will get answer- ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¹Ã…â€œHilsa is my most favorite fish&acute; and Maximum \r\npeople like ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¹Ã…â€œHilsa Fry&acute;, its really delicious testy dish. Anybody can \r\neasily cook it on home. If you want to test it just follow the given \r\nrecipe.<br><br><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Ingredients for Hilsa Fry (Ilish Vaja):</b><br>\r\n1 Hilsa fish<br>\r\nRed Chilly powder to test<br>\r\nTurmeric powder to test<br>\r\nOil as required<br>\r\nSalt to taste<br>\r\nOnion barista (fried slice onion)<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Method of Preparation (How to Cook):</b><br>\r\n<br>\r\n01. First cut the Hilsa into pieces and clean finely.<br>\r\n02. Mix finely the chili powder and turmeric powder and salt with Hilsa (fish), and then marinate the fish for 20-25 minutes.<br>\r\n04. Now heat the oil in a fry pan, and add pieces of Hilsa (fish).<br>\r\n05. Fry the fish until turns to crispy and brown color.<br>\r\n06. Transfer fish on paper towel for drain the excess oil.<br>\r\n07. Garnish with the onion barista and serve hot with rice.<br>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-01 07:15:36','smallCONT-00168life-ilsha.jpg','midCONT-00168life-ilsha.jpg','bigCONT-00168life-ilsha.jpg','USR-000001','2014-01-01 07:18:19','USR-000001',0),('CONT-00169',NULL,'5 Reasons to Go Camping','','Sure, camping is a budget-friendly vacation, but its benefits go beyond \r\nfinances. It provides the opportunity to disconnect from technology&nbsp;and spend quality time outdoors with friends and family. You&acute;re getting\r\n a healthy dose of Vitamin D from the sun, reducing mental stress by \r\ncommuning with nature and taking time to enjoy the simple things in \r\nlife. Not convinced yet? Here are five more reasons to go.<div><br></div><div><b>You Don&acute;t Have To Be A Pro</b></div><div>Camping isn&acute;t just for Boy Scouts and hardcore mountain men. There are \r\nplenty of campgrounds around the country for beginners, too. The <a href=\"http://www.campsitephotos.com/campground-information/Lake-Powell-Wahweap\" target=\"_blank\">Wahweap Campground Glen Park National Recreation Area</a>\r\n at Lake Powell is one of those spots. It&acute;s a quiet and impressive \r\nwaterfront area that&acute;s also comfortable, thanks to the hot showers and \r\nshaded picnic tables. You can even rent a boat or kayak at the onsite \r\nmarina to explore Lake Powell&acute;s stunning rock formations, which <i>Sunset </i>magazine compares to ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Zion National Park filled halfway with water.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â</div><div><br></div><div><p><b>It&acute;s GlamorousÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦Really!</b><br>\r\nEver heard of glamping? Yes, it&acute;s an actual thing. Basically, it&acute;s a \r\nluxury alternative to traditional camping. So instead of an RV or \r\nstandard tent, you&acute;re living it up in style with plush amenities. At <a href=\"http://www.pawsup.com/\" target=\"_blank\">The Resort at Paws Up</a>\r\n in Montana, River Camp puts you on the banks of the legendary Blackfoot\r\n River in a one- or two-bedroom tent with an en-suite bathroom. In your \r\ncozy home away from home, you&acute;ll enjoy comfortable beds, daily \r\nhousekeeping, a nightly s&acute;mores bonfire and even your very own camping \r\nbutler and chef.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Camping Is Romantic</strong><br>\r\nWhat could be more enchanting than a night spent under the stars with \r\nthe one you love? Chilly evenings perfect for cuddling, wide open spaces\r\n to admire, and nothing but conversation to keep you busy ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ camping is \r\npractically perfect for couples. Napa Valley&acute;s rolling hills and \r\nvineyards are a favorite camping destination for romance, because you \r\nhave the best of both worlds: quiet seclusion and access to the region&acute;s\r\n best wineries. <a href=\"http://www.skylinepark.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Skyline Wilderness Park</a> is just two miles from the center of downtown Napa and has trails for <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/yoga-fitness/go-mountain-hiking-or-trekking\">hiking</a>, biking and horseback riding.</p><p><strong>You Can Bring Your Dog</strong><br>\r\nThe beauty of camping is that you can bring the whole <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/pregnancy-parenting/5-essential-tips-for-healthy-and-happy-traveling-with-your-family\">family</a>,\r\n including your pup. Dog-friendly campgrounds are aplenty in states like\r\n California, Washington, Arizona and Colorado. For RV owners, the <a href=\"http://www.koa.com/campgrounds/san-francisco\" target=\"_blank\">North Petaluma KOA</a>\r\n site in Northern California is just 30 miles from the Golden Gate \r\nBridge, where both you and Fido are welcome on most of the Bay Area&acute;s \r\nparks and trails. Then there&acute;s <a href=\"http://www.route66koa.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Route 66 KOA</a>, which sits on the longest stretch of the historic highway and is near landmarks like the Hoover Dam and Havasu Falls.</p><p>TRY: <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/eating-healthy/healthy-snacks-happy-trail-mix\">Healthy Snacks For Happy Trails</a></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><strong><b>It&acute;s A Thrill</b><br>\r\n</strong>Is rugged adventure more your thing? There&acute;s plenty of \r\nopportunity for that on your next trip to Hawaii, where state \r\nrecreational areas offer the perfect retreat for experienced campers. On\r\n the Big Island, the <a href=\"http://www.hawaiistateparks.org/parks/hawaii/index.cfm?park_id=52\" target=\"_blank\">MacKenzie State Recreation Area</a>\r\n is a favorite of outdoor enthusiasts for its craggy coastline and \r\nelectrifying ocean views. If you like fishing and feeling like you&acute;re \r\naway from the everyday hustle, this is the place for you, although we \r\nshould point out that swimming isn&acute;t recommended here because of strong \r\ncurrents.</p></div>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 07:50:25','smallCONT-00169SMALL_shutterstock_62371906.jpg','midCONT-00169SMALL_shutterstock_62371906.jpg','bigCONT-00169SMALL_shutterstock_62371906.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00170',NULL,'Guide to Better Sleep, Naturally','','As adults, we all know that we should be averaging 7 to 9 hours of sleep\r\n per night. But be honest; how often does that really happen? Life is \r\nfull of distractions that can get in the way of a healthy sleep pattern.\r\n Still, getting a good night&acute;s rest is important to your health. Studies\r\n have shown a link between insufficient sleep and major health issues \r\nlike heart disease, diabetes and obesity. Good sleep can help with \r\nchronic pain, lower your risk of injury and improve your sex life. Yes, \r\nthat&acute;s right ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ feeling rested can increase your libido.','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 07:52:54','smallCONT-00170SMALL_shutterstock_80758018.jpg','midCONT-00170SMALL_shutterstock_80758018.jpg','bigCONT-00170SMALL_shutterstock_80758018.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',1),('CONT-00171',NULL,'Healing QA',' How To Fight Sleep Apnea?','<p>Ayurveda instructs individuals to identify the root cause of a \r\ndisease before addressing it through different therapies and remedies, \r\nas it is important to shape the regimen around resolving whatever issues\r\n lie beneath the symptoms. It is particularly important to keep this in \r\nmind when responding to sleep apnea, for this particular condition can \r\nbe caused by a variety of different factors. While of course being \r\noverweight is a common influence over such a disease, there are other \r\nconsiderations as well. An Ayurvedic practitioner will work with a sleep\r\n apnea sufferer to determine what imbalances they may be experiencing in\r\n their doshas. If they suffer from sleep apnea and are also particularly\r\n overweight, then they likely have excessive amounts of Kapha energy in \r\ntheir system and will then need to go on a Kapha-reducing diet as well \r\nas make other lifestyle changes.</p>\r\n<p>However, it is always beneficial to train oneself to use the full \r\nbreath during the day, and breathing properly and building the \r\nefficiency of the respiratory system as a whole during daylight hours \r\nwill also have a positive impact on the system&acute;s capacity to operate at \r\nnight. To practice the full breath, find a quiet place to sit in the \r\nmorning and sit upright either on a cushion on the floor or on the edge \r\nof a chair. Inhale through the nose for a few counts, and then exhale \r\nthrough the nose for twice as many counts. Allow the abdomen to expand \r\nas you inhale, and allow it to contract as you exhale. Be sure not to \r\nforce it.</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 07:56:53','smallCONT-00171healing3_womanheadmassage_cropped_full_13523041561.jpg','midCONT-00171healing3_womanheadmassage_cropped_full_13523041561.jpg','bigCONT-00171healing3_womanheadmassage_cropped_full_13523041561.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',1),('CONT-00172',NULL,'Healing QA: Natural Treatments For Cataracts?','Is there anything that can be done to heal cataracts naturally?','Ayurveda provides us with a number of different therapies that are \r\nuseful in helping to resolve cataracts that usually involve a \r\ncombination of different herbs, ghee, milk, sesame oil, honey, and other\r\n substances. What is particularly significant about cataracts, though, \r\nis that the nature of the symptoms (the color of the pupils, the texture\r\n and color of the patches, etc.) wind up playing a particularly \r\nsignificant role in how the issue is addressed. And, believe it or not, \r\nthere are Ayurvedic forms of surgery that are indicated for many of \r\nthese forms of the disease.','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:00:28','smallCONT-00172healing_mortar_and_pestle_with_greens_full_13512689241.jpg','midCONT-00172healing_mortar_and_pestle_with_greens_full_13512689241.jpg','bigCONT-00172healing_mortar_and_pestle_with_greens_full_13512689241.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00173',NULL,'Tips To Feel Young at Any Age','','<p>Do you ever feel like it&acute;s too late to get healthy and start a new \r\nexercise routine? That your body is not cooperating with you anymore and\r\n you&acute;ll never be able to lose weight? Or maybe you know someone who uses\r\n their age as an excuse to give up on their health?</p>\r\n<p>We&acute;re all scared, at least to some degree, to get older. We&acute;re afraid\r\n to lose our young energy, our young body, and may think that life is \r\nnot as bright around the corner. It&acute;s undeniable that time has an \r\nimmense power over our body and mind but it&acute;s also true that we have the\r\n power to significantly slow all the aging processes down. We can keep \r\nour body fit and healthy and enjoy life no matter the age. It&acute;s a matter\r\n of belief and daily actions.</p><p> <strong>Taking Care Of Yourself: It&acute;s Never Too Late</strong> </p><p>\r\n</p><p> Very few of us have the willpower to adopt new health habits in the \r\n2nd half of our life and a very small percentage of those stick with it!\r\n In reality you can get fit whenever you want, it&acute;s a matter of \r\nintention. Don&acute;t ever create a mental block or say I can&acute;t because it&acute;s \r\ntoo late. Now is just the right time, whatever your age is!</p><p>&nbsp;The truth of the matter is it&acute;s never too late to reverse the age \r\nand start taking care of our ingeniously built body. If you want to get \r\nhealthy and get your young body and energy back &nbsp;Then follow this few \r\ntips to stay in shape at any age:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><b>Move every day</b>. Choose the activity that you like and stick \r\nwith it. Yoga, weights, cardio, stairs. Whatever you prefer, make no \r\nexcuses to stay lazy! There is nothing more precious than health and you\r\n need to be healthy to enjoy life. Being 45 is not an excuse to turn \r\nyour back on your health and looks! As one teacher said: ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“You need to \r\nmeditate daily for half an hour, if you don&acute;t have time, you need to \r\nmeditate twice a day!ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â This saying is true for any self-improvement \r\nmethod, including yoga, running, push ups, or whatever you choose to do!\r\n And you don&acute;t have to do any of this on your own. Most exercise is a \r\nlot more fun in a group or in a pair (ever hear of <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/yoga-fitness/couples-yoga-not-just-for-lovers\">couples yoga</a>?)</li>\r\n<li><b>Laugh a lot</b>. We all know that laughing prolongs life, \r\nproduces happiness hormones, and turns any situation better. Did you \r\nknow that laughing also burns calories, creates stronger and flatter \r\nabs, and provides a workout for all the facial muscles? Look for funny, \r\nhappy things around you and you will laugh more often which in turn will\r\n make you a happier person. Focus on the positive!</li>\r\n<li><b>Surround yourself with young hearts</b>. Surround yourself with \r\npeople who are strong, healthy and young at heart. Whether it&acute;s a young \r\nfitness trainer, who challenges you every day and or a group of people \r\nwho do yoga or hike together. Young energy is catching! Who do you \r\nsurround yourself with?</li>\r\n<li><b>Don&acute;t be afraid to be a student.</b> Keep an open mind. Quite \r\noften people think that they&acute;re done learning and developing after their\r\n traditional schooling and education is over. In reality there&acute;s never \r\nan end to learning. If you stay still while the whole world is moving \r\nforward, you stay behind. This is true for any field of life ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Â from \r\nhealth research to philosophy. A good way to keep learning is to read \r\nand to discuss new ideas.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;Stay inspired and enjoy your life at any age!</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:06:17','smallCONT-00173photo_feel_young_at_any_age_cropped_full_13419396211.jpg','midCONT-00173photo_feel_young_at_any_age_cropped_full_13419396211.jpg','bigCONT-00173photo_feel_young_at_any_age_cropped_full_13419396211.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00174',NULL,'4 Simple Tips for Unplugging','','<p>Give yourself a reprieve from the electronic blizzard, rings&nbsp;and dings of modern day.&nbsp; Here are a few helpful tips.</p>\r\n<p><b><br>\r\n1.&nbsp; Don&acute;t use your mobile device for your alarm clock.</b> The \r\ntemptation to wake up and immediately check the myriad of communications\r\n on your mobile device is great ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ be it new emails, your Facebook or \r\nInstagram feed, or the latest tweets and Pins.&nbsp; Resist the urge. Those \r\nfirst waking moments of your morning are precious.&nbsp; It is the time when \r\nyou begin a brand new day, in own your space, set your daily intention \r\nand move through your life from a place of power.&nbsp; Allowing this time to\r\n be overrun by mindless social posts from others and emails wrought with\r\n responsibility, sets you up for stress for the rest of the day.</p>\r\n<p><b>2. Create a time block of ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“e-freenessÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â with your family.</b>&nbsp;\r\n Pick a time each day, especially on the weekends when your family is \r\nmore likely all together, and deem this an electronic-free zone.&nbsp; This \r\nis the time where you talk, play, cuddle, and do anything besides use \r\nsomething electronic.&nbsp; This will help foster more authentic closeness, \r\nwithout distraction.</p>\r\n<p><b>3. Create boundaries.</b>&nbsp; On your \r\noutgoing message or email signature, tell people exactly what to expect \r\nfrom your communication.&nbsp; For example, you could inform others that, ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“I \r\ncheck these messages twice a day, at noon and at 5p.m. and I look \r\nforward to getting back to you as soon as possible.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â Or, on your email \r\nsignature, you could do the same thing.&nbsp; This will stop the endless and \r\nobsessive ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“checkingÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â of communications, and will create clearer \r\nboundaries for those who need you to get back to them.</p>\r\n<p><b>4.&nbsp; Take an e-vacation.</b>&nbsp; You will be\r\n amazed at what you start to notice, feel and think about again if you \r\ntake a more significant vacation from tweets, posts, notes, and texts. \r\nYou might fall in love with your mate all over againÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¦or even yourself, \r\nthe earth and the wonder of it all.&nbsp; You might get inspired to do \r\nsomething creative like write, sing, paint or play.&nbsp; Don&acute;t be surprised \r\nif you experience some withdrawal; it&acute;s going to be okay, and it&acute;s \r\nactually one of the best things you can do for yourself.</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:11:04','smallCONT-00174laptop_handcuff.jpg','midCONT-00174laptop_handcuff.jpg','bigCONT-00174laptop_handcuff.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',1),('CONT-00175',NULL,'Stomach Virus: Best Natural Home Remedies','','<h1><span style=\"color: #464646; font-family: HelveticaNeue, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 1px; text-align: justify;\">Stomach\r\n virus, also known as gastroenteritis, stomach flu, or gastric flu, is \r\nan infection that causes inflammation of the gastrointestinal tract, \r\nwhich affects the stomach and the intestines. Although it is a viral \r\ninfection, it should not be confused with the influenza virus, or flu \r\nviruses.</span></h1>\r\n<div class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" id=\"attachment_1158\"><img class=\"attachment-medium\" alt=\"stomach_virus_full_1332267931.jpg\" src=\"http://i1.wp.com/www.veria.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/stomach_virus_full_13322679311.jpg?resize=200%2C300\" height=\"300\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<p>A stomach virus usually lasts from 2-5 days and is self-limiting, \r\nwhich means the body cures itself. It is highly contagious, and common \r\namong adults and children. Stomach virus infections occur all \r\nyear-round. They go away on their own eventually, and there are several \r\nnatural remedies to relieve symptoms. Severe cases may also occur, but \r\nare rare.</p>\r\n<h2>Stomach Virus: Causes</h2>\r\n<p>Stomach viruses are highly contagious. They are spread by coming into\r\n contact with someone or something that is contaminated such as food, \r\ndrink, feces, soiled diapers, bodily fluids including vomit and saliva, \r\ncooking utensils or cutlery. They are sometimes called a ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“family affairÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â\r\n because they tend to spread to the whole household once one person in a\r\n family is affected. And even after the symptoms subside, they don&acute;t go \r\naway immediately ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Â the virus can survive in feces for up to two weeks \r\nafter recovery.</p>\r\n<p>READ: <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/healing/stomach-flu-preventing-a-common-illness\" target=\"_blank\">Stomach Flu: Preventing a Common Illness&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n<p>Public places that are frequented by children are particularly \r\nsusceptible to stomach viruses, such as nurseries, day care centers, \r\nschools, camps, and dormitories. And they can easily spread in eating \r\nestablishments, such as restaurants and cafes that do not have thorough \r\nand correct sanitization practices.</p>\r\n<p>There are four kinds of viruses that cause stomach virus:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Adenovirus</strong>. This is common in children under 2 \r\nyears old. This specific strain attacks the infant&acute;s gastrointestinal \r\ntract, which then causes diarrhea and vomiting. Symptoms appear a week \r\nafter initial exposure to this virus. Infections of this type occur \r\nyear-round.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Astrovirus</strong>. This particular type of strain is also \r\ncommon in infants, children, and the elderly. Symptoms usually appear \r\n1-3 days after initial exposure to this virus. Infections of this type \r\nare common during the cold winter months.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Caliciviruses</strong>. Caliciviruses affect people of all \r\nages. They are further divided into four types, the most common of which\r\n are the noroviruses. Noroviruses are the culprit for stomach virus \r\nepidemics or outbreaks, most active within the months of October to \r\nApril. Symptoms usually appear 1-3 days after initial exposure to this \r\nvirus.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Rotavirus</strong>. This specific strain is known to be the \r\nmost common cause of stomach flu among infants 3-15 months old, and \r\nyoung children under 5 years old. Symptoms appear after 1-2 days of \r\ninitial exposure to this virus, causing 3-8 days of watery diarrhea and \r\nvomiting, with fever and occasional abdominal pain. It is highly \r\ncontagious and it can easily transfer to adult caretakers and those in \r\nclose contact with the infected child. However, with adults, the \r\nsymptoms are milder. Rotavirus infections usually occur from November to\r\n April.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Stomach Virus: Symptoms</h2>\r\n<p>Common symptoms of a stomach virus are nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, \r\nand abdominal cramps. Other symptoms may include the following: mild \r\nfever, headaches, chills, fatigue, muscle pains, and occasionally bloody\r\n diarrhea. Usually, symptoms appear 48 hours after initial exposure to \r\nthe virus. Symptoms last for 2-5 days, or in serious cases, for up to 10\r\n days.</p>\r\n<h2>Stomach Virus: Diagnostic Tests</h2>\r\n<p>Stomach viruses cannot be cured by antibiotics or other medications \r\nsince they aren&acute;t caused by bacteria. They are self-limiting: nearly all\r\n cases of stomach virus resolve by themselves after a few days. However,\r\n you should call a doctor if:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You&acute;re not able to keep liquids down for 24 hours</li>\r\n<li>You&acute;ve been vomiting for more than 48 hours</li>\r\n<li>You&acute;re vomiting or excreting blood</li>\r\n<li>You have a swollen stomach or abdominal pain</li>\r\n<li>You&acute;re dehydrated ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Â characteristic signs include weakness, \r\nlightheadedness, decreased urination, dry skin, dry mouth and lack of \r\nsweat and tears.</li>\r\n<li>You have a fever above 104 F (40 C).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Doctors base their diagnosis of stomach virus on the basis of a \r\nphysical exam, your symptoms, and complete medical history. You may be \r\nasked for a blood test. Sometimes, a stool sample is needed to rule out \r\nother possible causes. A stool test can also test for the presence of \r\nthe rotavirus, although it does not identify other virus strains.</p>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2>Stomach Virus: Treatment Options</h2>\r\n<div class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" id=\"attachment_1159\"><img class=\"attachment-medium\" alt=\"shutterstock124367428_full_1374865506.jpg\" src=\"http://i1.wp.com/www.veria.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/shutterstock124367428_full_1374865506.jpg?resize=199%2C300\" height=\"300\" width=\"199\">\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Stomach virus is self-limiting ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Â it resolves by itself without any \r\nneed for antibiotics or any other medication. Treatment focuses on \r\nalleviating the symptoms, discomfort and pain. Preventing dehydration is\r\n also essential as the symptoms of stomach virus ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Â vomiting, sweating \r\nand diarrhea ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ all cause loss of fluids.</p>\r\n<p>Dehydration symptoms include excessive thirst, dry mouth, lethargy or\r\n severe weakness, lightheadedness or dizziness, little, dark or no \r\nurine. Children are most susceptible, although any one is at risk.</p>\r\n<p>As well as water, you can try sipping electrolyte drinks such as \r\nPedialyte or Gatorade every 10 or 15 minutes to rehydrate. The small \r\nsips are helpful if you are vomiting to prevent the stomach from being \r\noverloaded.</p>\r\n<p>While there aren&acute;t any medications that will cure a stomach virus, there are plenty of home remedies. Here are some top tips:</p>\r\n<p>WATCH: &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.veria.com/video/dandelion-leaf-food-allergy-smoothie\" target=\"_blank\">Dandelion Leaf Food Allergy Smoothie</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>No food</strong>: Start with a fluid diet and avoid solid food for a few hours to allow your stomach to settle.</li>\r\n<li><strong>BRAT Diet</strong>: Observe no solid food for four hours \r\nthen gradually reintroduce easily digestible food like bananas, rice, \r\napples, toast, broth, and crackers. Clinicians recommend the BRAT diet \r\n(bananas, rice, apples and toast) for a day or two before or until your \r\nsymptoms subside.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Electrolyte Replacement Sips</strong>: Sip small amounts of \r\npedialyte or diluted gatorade in frequent intervals. (Just water alone \r\ncause sodium levels to decrease and lead to worsened dehydration and \r\nbrain issues).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Rest and relaxation</strong>: Having stomach virus can sap up all of your energy, so it&acute;s advisable to sleep as much as possible.</li>\r\n<li><strong>No irritating foods</strong>: Avoid the following: dairy \r\nproducts, caffeine, alcohol, oily and fried food, tomato-based food, \r\nspicy food, carbonated or sugared drinks, sour juices. Also, no not suck\r\n on ice chips, which can actually worsen vomiting because they make your\r\n stomach feel fuller than it is.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Stomach Virus: Natural and Homeopathic Remedies</h2>\r\n<p>Natural and homeopathic remedies can also help alleviate the symptoms\r\n without the risk of the more harmful side effects of stronger \r\nmedications. The following are recommended:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Ginger root</strong>. Powdered ginger root can be made into \r\nhot tea by adding boiling water. In China, it has a long history as \r\ntraditional home remedy for morning sickness, motion sickness, and \r\nnausea. But it should be noted that once your vomiting ginger can lead \r\nto worsened esophageal reflux.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Peppermint</strong>. Peppermint is a pleasant-tasting herbal\r\n alternative that relieves all kinds of tummy-related aches and pains. \r\nAs a hot tea, peppermint acts as an anti-spasmodic, which means it can \r\nrelieve stomach, intestinal cramps and hyperacidity. It is also a \r\ncarminative, which means it can help dispel gas and bloating in the \r\ndigestive system.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Chamomile</strong>. Chamomile can also help reduce stomach \r\nvirus-related symptoms like nausea, cramping, bloating, and gas. It has \r\nanti-spasmodic and anti-inflammatory properties, making it particularly \r\neffective in soothing stomach and intestinal cramps. It is also an \r\nanti-microbial agent, so it reduces internal infections and \r\ninflammations, especially when combined with other anti-microbial plants\r\n like thyme or Echinacea. It has calming properties and a mild, soothing\r\n taste, which makes it suitable for children.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Stomach Virus: Prevention</h2>\r\n<p>There&acute;s no effective treatment for viral gastroenteritis, so prevention is key.</p>\r\n<p>WATCH: &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.veria.com/video/peggy-ks-kitchen-cures-recipe-pomegranate-ginger-yogurt-good-for-digestion\" target=\"_blank\">Pomegranate Ginger Yogurt ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ Good For Digestion</a></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Frequent hand washing</strong>: especially when you prepare \r\nfood or after using the toilet. Make sure to wash around the cuticles \r\nand beneath your fingernails. If you have children, it&acute;s important you \r\nteach them how and when to wash their hands.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Avoid sharing cooking utensils</strong>: Gastroenteritis can be transmitted through contaminated food and cooking utensils. Avoid sharing utensils.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Keep Your Distance</strong>: Avoid close contact with anyone\r\n who has the virus, if possible. Wash your hands with soap and water \r\nafter being in contact with anyone who has had the virus.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Disinfect Surfaces</strong>: Regularly disinfect easily accessible surfaces such as countertops, tables, and baby changing stations.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Travelling Precautions</strong>: if you are travelling to a \r\ndeveloping country, it&acute;s important that you take extra precautions \r\naround hygiene and food and drink consumption. Make sure you only drink \r\nbottled water, and do not eat any raw foods, such as salads. Use bottled\r\n water to brush your teeth. Ask for your drinks without ice cubes, \r\nunless you are positive that the water has been sterilized.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Stomach virus is one of the most common illnesses. The great majority\r\n of cases are non-life threatening and resolve by themselves after 2-5 \r\ndays. Although they require no particular medication or treatment, there\r\n a number of home and natural remedies to ease the symptoms and prevent \r\ndehydration</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:20:03','smallCONT-00175SMALL_shutterstock_105902354.jpg','midCONT-00175SMALL_shutterstock_105902354.jpg','bigCONT-00175SMALL_shutterstock_105902354.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00176',NULL,'9 Art and Animal Therapy Programs For Kids','','Raising a child in today&acute;s world is no easy feat. Sometimes, what your \r\nfamily or little one needs is a fresh and creative outlet. Art and \r\nanimal therapy programs are a great way to instill confidence and \r\npromote healing. First, caring for a pet is a rewarding experience for \r\nkids. They learn empathy, responsibility and respect for other living \r\ncreatures ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ but most importantly, they learn how to love and be loved. \r\nSecond, art can be just the release children need to deal with emotional\r\n or behavioral challenges. By offering a safe environment in which to \r\nexplore creativity, art promotes healing and imparts a sense of purpose.\r\n Help your child discover freedom and joy with one of our favorite art \r\nand animal therapy programs.','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:32:16','smallCONT-00176art_and_animal_therapy_programs_for_kids_full_1374075939.jpg','midCONT-00176art_and_animal_therapy_programs_for_kids_full_1374075939.jpg','bigCONT-00176art_and_animal_therapy_programs_for_kids_full_1374075939.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00177',NULL,'Healing QA: How Can I Treat Migraines?','I suffer from really bad migraines, sometimes for days at a time. What can I do to get rid of them (aside from quitting my job)?','Ayurveda considers most migraines to be triggered by either an excessive\r\n amount of movement and dryness as indicated by Vata imbalances, or by \r\nan excessive amount of heat as indicated by Pitta imbalances. If the \r\nmigraines are accompanied by constipation, insomnia, and sharp, shooting\r\n bursts of pain, then they are likely based on a Vata imbalance and may \r\nbe resolved with the consumption of oils like olive oil and sesame oil \r\nas well as the application of these oils to the skin. If the migraines \r\nare accompanied by burning sensations, profuse sweat, and irritability, \r\nthen they are more likely based on a Pitta imbalance and may be resolved\r\n with the consumption of cooling foods like cow&acute;s milk and basmati rice \r\nas well as a reduction in physical exertion overall.','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:35:39','smallCONT-00177SMALL_shutterstock_142814569.jpg','midCONT-00177SMALL_shutterstock_142814569.jpg','bigCONT-00177SMALL_shutterstock_142814569.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00178',NULL,'Brain Games: How To Improve Your Memory','','<p>As we get older, our memories start to slip. We forget where we put \r\nour car keys and can&acute;t remember what we were supposed to buy at the \r\ngrocery store. It happens to everyone.</p>\r\n<p>Still, memory loss is not something we should take lightly. Keeping \r\nyour brain strong throughout life can help you stay healthy as you age. \r\nIt&acute;s also important in preventing diseases like <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/video/animal-therapy-for-alzheimers-disease\">Alzheimer&acute;s</a> and other forms of dementia.</p>\r\n<p>Strengthening your brain&acute;s function isn&acute;t as difficult as you might \r\nthink. I asked Jessica Langbaum, PhD and principal scientist for the <a href=\"http://www.banneralz.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Banner Alzheimer&acute;s Institute</a>, for her advice on improving memory. Here&acute;s what she had to say.</p>\r\n<p><b>Go Play</b></p><p>\r\nWhether or not ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“brain gamesÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â have a positive effect on memory loss \r\nprevention is a contested topic in the medical world. Unless they are \r\nbased on scientific findings, a phone app or computer game probably \r\nwon&acute;t help improve overall brain function ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ it will only strengthen your\r\n ability to perform tasks associated with that game.</p>\r\n<p>However, a good ol&acute; crossword puzzle or game of Scrabble or Sudoku \r\nmay be just what the doctor ordered. That&acute;s because they are similar to \r\nthe types of games that were developed in labs by doctors specifically \r\nfor brain research, says Langbaum.</p>\r\n<p>WATCH: <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/video/peggy-ks-kitchen-cures-recipe-spinach-beet-salad-purple-corn-green-tea-spritzer\">Fight Alzheimer&acute;s With Spinach Beet Salad</a> (VIDEO)</p>\r\n<p>ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“I like to stress that people should try new<i> </i>things,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â she \r\nadds. ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“If you&acute;re really good at crosswords, try something different. \r\nIt&acute;s almost as if you&acute;re exercising your muscles. If you&acute;re doing the \r\nsame exercise over and over, your body gets used to it, and the impact \r\nisn&acute;t the same. It&acute;s good to present your brain with new challenges.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â</p>\r\n<p>So when it comes to brain games, it&acute;s not so much the act of playing \r\nthat&acute;s good for memory ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ it&acute;s the practice of teaching your mind a <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/video/music-lessons-boost-verbal-memory-skills\">new skill</a>.</p>\r\n<p><b>Be Social</b><br>\r\nAs it turns out, having a tight circle of friends isn&acute;t great just for \r\nyour social life ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ it&acute;s important to your health, too. Being socially \r\nactive helps keep your brain sharp.</p>\r\n<p><b></b>Researchers aren&acute;t exactly sure why, but it most likely has to\r\n do with the fact that friends provide emotional support, help bring \r\nmeaning to everyday life and, well, make you laugh. Plus, think about \r\nall of the healthy debates you&acute;ve had with your pals over the years \r\nabout movies and politics. These intellectual conversations keep you on \r\nyour toes.</p>\r\n<p><b></b>Again, Langbaum emphasizes the importance of getting out of \r\nyour comfort zone. Putting yourself in new social situations works out \r\nyour brain muscles. In particular, Langbaum says that volunteering \r\nbenefits <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/healing/ginkgo-biloba-and-other-natural-memory-boosters\">memory</a>\r\n and brain ability ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ helping out in a classroom, teaching kids how to \r\nread or write. You&acute;re thinking strategically and interacting with \r\npeople. It&acute;s a win-win.</p><p><b>Eat Healthy</b></p><p>\r\nÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“Diet is very important for brain function,ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â says Langbaum. ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“I always tell people ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œ what&acute;s heart healthy is brain healthy.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â</p>\r\n<p>Your brain controls every one of your bodily functions, so you want \r\nto make sure it&acute;s getting all of the nutrients it needs to stay strong. \r\nThe four most important elements in your brain&acute;s ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“dietÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â are glucose for \r\nenergy, fatty acids like omega-3 to strengthen the synapses, amino acids\r\n for connecting its neurotransmitters and antioxidants to regulate \r\nstress and protect brain cells.</p>\r\n<p>So what are some of those brain-boosting foods? Eggs, for starters, \r\nwhich are rich in protein and can improve overall cognitive performance.\r\n Healthy carbohydrates like oats are good, too, because they provide \r\nglucose that fuels your brain. And then there are lentils for Vitamin B,\r\n flaxseed because of its healthy fat content, walnuts for antioxidants \r\nand omega-3s and beets to increase blood flow to the brain.</p>\r\n<p><b>Stay Active</b><br>\r\nReally, the benefits of exercise are endless. When it comes to cognitive\r\n function, exercise is healthy because it increases blood flow to the \r\nbrain and releases chemicals that improve your mind&acute;s ability to \r\nconcentrate.</p>\r\n<p>Frequent activity also increases the brain&acute;s levels of serotonin and \r\ndopamine, which are the chemicals responsible for regulating your mood. \r\nDeficiencies or low levels of serotonin and dopamine are what cause \r\nmental conditions like anxiety and depression, so you want to keep those\r\n levels high!</p>\r\n<p>Working out also boosts your energy and immune system. It makes you \r\nfeel confident, and enhances decision-making, higher thinking and \r\nlearning abilities.</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:41:23','smallCONT-00178How-to-Improve-Your-Memory-Be-Social.jpg','midCONT-00178How-to-Improve-Your-Memory-Be-Social.jpg','bigCONT-00178How-to-Improve-Your-Memory-Be-Social.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00179',NULL,'How To Treat Eczema Naturally','','<p>n my private practice, some of the most difficult conditions to treat are those having to do with <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/wellness/holistic-approach-autumn-skin-care/\">skin</a>.\r\n Even though they are on the outside of the body, I find skin conditions\r\n require an astute clinical acumen to understand what is causing them \r\nfrom the inside.</p>\r\n<p>Eczema is a good example. Also known as atopic dermatitis, eczema is a\r\n condition in which the skin develops areas of scaly and itchy rashes. \r\nIt&acute;s been known to develop as a result of an allergic reaction and can \r\nbecome a chronic condition if not treated in a comprehensive manner.</p>\r\n<p>Eczema can occur on almost any part of the body but is most commonly \r\nexperienced on the scalp, elbows, face, ankles and hands. It will often \r\ncome and go, and sometimes accompany other allergic ailments like <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/video/asthma-a-holistic-view/\">asthma</a>. In some cases, certain soaps, detergents, metals, dust mites or animal dander can trigger eczema.</p>\r\nFor some people, it is a food or lack of nutrients allergen that \r\ncauses the reaction. Sometimes worsened by dry climates, eczema also can\r\n be brought on by exposure to water, temperature changes and stress.\r\n<p>Conventional eczema treatment usually consists of steroid or other \r\ntypes of creams that help relieve the subsequent itching and \r\ninflammation. In severe cases, an oral steroid might be necessary. \r\nHowever, these ointments and medications can have negative side effects \r\nsuch as skin thinning. Therefore, they are not recommended for long-term\r\n use.</p>\r\n<p>Newer prescription creams, called calcineurin inhibitors, are also \r\navailable. They work by moderating the body&acute;s immune response. Although \r\nthese drugs don&acute;t have the same side effects as steroids, their \r\nlong-term safety isn&acute;t yet clear.</p>\r\nAs a <a href=\"http://www.veria.com/video/sneak-peek-myth-defying-with-dr-holly/\">natural medicine</a> practitioner, I typically recommend a more comprehensive approach tapered to each individual. Here are some common examples:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>I find that putting someone on a diet specific to their blood type \r\nhelps to eliminate potential food sensitivities and triggers. I also \r\nencourage whole foods rich in essential fats, vitamin A and silicon.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.veria.com/wellness/evening-primrose-oil-and-other-essential-oils-for-sensitive-skin/\">Evening primrose oil</a>\r\n at 4 to 6 grams a day for adults and 2 to 4 grams for children helps \r\nimmensely with the inflammation and itching. (Allow 3 to 4 months for \r\nfull effect.)</li>\r\n<li>Quercetin at 500 milligrams three times a day between meals helps to stabilize mast cells, which react to allergens.</li>\r\n<li>Chamomile is widely used in Europe for the treatment of skin \r\nirritation and topical chamomile creams work wonders for non-toxic \r\nrelief from the itching and scabbing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Treating a skin condition like eczema is an ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“inside-outÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â <i>and</i> \r\nan ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“outside-inÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â job! Identifying and treating the cause while also \r\nreplenishing nutrients and safely managing inflammation helps resolve \r\neczema without the harmful side effects.</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:48:41','smallCONT-00179How-To-Treat-Eczema-Naturally-Evening-Primrose-Oil.jpg','midCONT-00179How-To-Treat-Eczema-Naturally-Evening-Primrose-Oil.jpg','bigCONT-00179How-To-Treat-Eczema-Naturally-Evening-Primrose-Oil.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00180',NULL,'How to Keep Your Cool Under Stress','','<p>With today&acute;s stressors being multiple, constant and prolonged, it is \r\nquite easy to loose your cool, which unfortunately just makes any \r\nsituation worse. I call it ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“short fuse syndrome.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚ÂSo how can you keep \r\nyour cool and ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“lengthen your fuseÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â during times of strife, such as your \r\ncommute in terrible traffic, dealing with angry clients or terrible \r\ncustomer service agents, handling aggressive co-workers or fussy family \r\nmembers?</p>\r\n<p>Believe it or not, the answer is in your brain. Yes, your brain!Your \r\nautomatic nervous system controls how your heart, stomach, and \r\nintestines function. It&acute;s divided into three parts, the sympathetic \r\nnervous system, which reacts to stress; the parasympathetic nervous \r\nsystem, which helps you relax; and the enteric nervous system, a network\r\n of nerve fibers.</p>\r\n<p>The sympathetic nervous system controls our response to the multiple,\r\n constant and prolonged stressors we deal with in our society, including\r\n the ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“fight or flightÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â response. The parasympathetic nervous system \r\nrules our ability to rest, relax and repair. These days, the imbalance \r\nin the activity of these two parts means that the sympathetic part of \r\nyour brain is getting way too much action, and the parasympathetic part \r\nis being completely left in the dust. However, you can successfully \r\nbalance this situation out by purposefully engaging in powerful \r\nparasympathetic behavior (PB).PB is different for everyone. It is that \r\nperson, place or thing that helps you unburden. For some people it is \r\ntaking a bath; for others, it is spending time with their grandchildren.\r\n I love to be outdoors near any type of wildlife. The key is to expose \r\nyourself daily to calming things and situations<i>.</i>I have noticed \r\nthat in order to do break this cycle and work towards creating a \r\nbalanced nervous system and therefore longer fuse, it isn&acute;t the quantity\r\n of time you spend in PB, but the quality and consistency.</p>\r\n<p>I have a patient who lives on the West Coast but works on the East \r\nCoast. Every morning, when he turned on his computer, he was greeted \r\nwith three hours of work, due to the time difference, and it was making \r\nhim a stress case. So we initiated a ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“power pauseÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â for his PB. Now, each\r\n morning before he turns on his computer, he stops, breathes deeply, \r\nreflects on his gratitude and purpose, reminds himself of what is really\r\n important and centers himself for his day. He started out doing this \r\nfor only three minutes at first, but he is now up to 20. He does it \r\ndaily, and he reports that it has helped him in all stressful \r\nsituations, because he feels more in ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“control.ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â WOW! I love that! It \r\ndoesn&acute;t take long to have the powerful parasympathetic part of your \r\nnervous system activated again to help you grow your fuse, balance your \r\nbrain and keep your cool!</p>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:50:22','smallCONT-00180shutterstock_88646935_B.jpg','midCONT-00180shutterstock_88646935_B.jpg','bigCONT-00180shutterstock_88646935_B.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0),('CONT-00181',NULL,'Samsung Galaxy S5 metal build confirmed by Vice President?','','<div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"clearfix eight_col\">\r\n<div id=\"news_article\">\r\n<div class=\"text_content\" itemprop=\"articleBody\">\r\n<p>Rumours that Samsung will opt for a premium metal build for the \r\nGalaxy S5 looked a smidgeon more nailed-on today, with the news that the\r\n company&acute;s Vice President has been spilling the beans about its plans at\r\n what sounds like a boozy soiree. </p>\r\n<p>A report in the Korean press claims that Dong-hoon Chang, Samsung&acute;s \r\nVice President and Head of Design Strategy, revealed (almost) all at a \r\nNew Year&acute;s Eve party at Seoul&acute;s Shilla Hotel. </p>\r\n<p>According to the site, Dong-hoon told the great and good assembled \r\nthat the Galaxy S5 will indeed be made out of ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“new materialÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â. That \r\nchimes with long-standing rumours that the next-gen Galaxy S smartphone \r\nwill ditch the range&acute;s plastic construction for a metal frame.</p>\r\n<p>Most recent reports indicate this could be <a href=\"http://www.uswitch.com/mobiles/news/2013/12/samsung_galaxy_s5_could_have_a_diamond_coated_body/\">diamond-coated metal</a>\r\n to make it extra tough and bring Samsung&acute;s flagship smartphone more in \r\nline with the much-praised aluminium unibody shell of HTC&acute;s One. </p>\r\n<p>But Dong-hoon wasn&acute;t done there. He also disclosed that chatter of a \r\nlaunch date for the Galaxy S5 at some time around Mobile World Congress \r\n(MWC) is ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã¢â‚¬Å“about rightÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â. </p>\r\n<p>So what to make of this? </p>\r\n<p>Well, while we think it&acute;s Samsung would ditch its habit of holding \r\nspecial one-off press events for Galaxy S handset launches to unveil its\r\n handset amid all the rival devices at MWC, his comments suggest to us \r\nthat a February/March release certainly isn&acute;t out of the question. </p>\r\n<p>This tallies with speculation that Samsung is <a href=\"http://www.uswitch.com/mobiles/news/2013/11/samsung_galaxy_s5_new_rumours_point_to_early_2014_release/\">moving the phone&acute;s release forward</a>, presumably to give it the largest sales window possible ahead of the release of a new iPhone in September.&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div>','General','General','','Same','Active','2014-01-04 08:59:31','smallCONT-00181samsung_galaxy_s5_mock_up_520x300x24_fill.jpg','midCONT-00181samsung_galaxy_s5_mock_up_520x300x24_fill.jpg','bigCONT-00181samsung_galaxy_s5_mock_up_520x300x24_fill.jpg','USR-000001','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',1);

